pace.definition: A single movement from one foot to the other in walking; a step.

pacemaker.definition: a specialized bit of heart tissue that controls the heartbeat.

pacific.definition: Of or pertaining to peace; of a peaceful character; not warlike; not quarrelsome; as, a pacific nature or condition.

pacifism.definition: the doctrine that all violence is unjustifiable.

pacifist.definition: A person opposed to violence as a means of settling disputes.

pacing.definition: the speed at which a composition is to be played.

packaged.definition: Enclosed in a package{2} or protective covering; as, packaged cereals.

packer.definition: A person whose business is to pack things; especially, one who packs food for preservation or for the market; as, a pork packer.

pact.definition: An agreement; a league; a compact; a covenant.

pain.definition: Punishment suffered or denounced; suffering or evil inflicted as a punishment for crime, or connected with the commission of a crime; penalty.

paintbrush.definition: A brush used to apply paint.

paired.definition: Organized into compatible pairs; -- used of gloves, socks, etc. See pair{1}, v. t.

palatinate.definition: The province or seigniory of a palatine; the dignity of a palatine.

palatine.definition: Of or pertaining to the palate; palatal.

pallet.definition: A small and mean bed; a bed of straw.

pallor.definition: Paleness; want of color; pallidity; as, pallor of the complexion.

palm.definition: The inner and somewhat concave part of the hand between the bases of the fingers and the wrist.

palpate.definition: To examine for medical purposes by touching, as of body parts; as, the nurse palpated the patient's stomach.

paltry.definition: Mean; vile; worthless; despicable; contemptible; pitiful; trifling; as, a paltry excuse; paltry gold.

panda.definition: A small Asiatic mammal (Ailurus fulgens) having fine soft fur, which inhabits the mountains of Northern India. It was once thought to be related to the bears, but is now believed to be more closely related to raccoons. It has reddish-brown fur on the back and sides, and black fur on the legs and underside. Called also the lesser panda.

paneled.definition: Decorated with panels or wainscoting; -- used of walls; as, a paneled family room.

paneling.definition: The act or process of forming in panels or decorating with panels.

pang.definition: A paroxysm of extreme pain or anguish; a sudden and transitory agony; a throe; as, the pangs of death.

panhandle.definition: To accost people in a public place and ask for money; to beg.

panicky.definition: Same as panic-stricken; as, the travellers became panicky as the snow deepened.

panning.definition: The act or process in which heavier ores are concentrated by agitating a sample of crushed ore under water in a shallow pan, thus washing away the lighter particles from the sample; as, panning for gold. See pan{1}, v. t. and pan{1}, v. i.

panting.definition: The act or process of breathing heavily, usually after exertion.

pants.definition: A garment extending from the waist to the knee or ankle, covering each leg separately.

panzer.definition: Equipped with armored vehicles; armored; as, a panzer division.

papaya.definition: A tree (Carica Papaya) of tropical America, belonging to the order Passiflore; called also papaw and pawpaw. It has a soft, spongy stem, eighteen or twenty feet high, crowned with a tuft of large, long-stalked, palmately lobed leaves. The milky juice of the plant is said to have the property of making meat tender.

paper.definition: To cover or line with paper, especially with wallpaper; to furnish with paper hangings; to wallpaper; as, to paper a room or a house.

paperback.definition: having a flexible binding; -- of books. Contrasted to hardcover or hardbacked or hardbound.

papers.definition: Documents providing information, esp. of an official nature about a person, vehicle, business, etc. See paper{9}, n.

paperwork.definition: Work that involves handling or writing documents such as forms, letters, reports, sales records, etc.

parachute.definition: TO descend to th ground from an airplane or other high place using a parachute; as, when the plane stalled, he parachuted safely to the ground.

paradox.definition: A tenet or proposition contrary to received opinion; an assertion or sentiment seemingly contradictory, or opposed to common sense; that which in appearance or terms is absurd, but yet may be true in fact.

paranoia.definition: A chronic form of insanity characterized by very gradual impairment of the intellect, systematized delusion, and usually by delusions of persecution or mandatory delusions producing homicidal tendency. In its mild form paranoia may consist in the well-marked crotchetiness exhibited in persons commonly called Webster 1913 Suppl.]

paranoid.definition: Affected with paranoia; as, a paranoid schizophrenic.

paranormal.definition: Of or pertaining to parapsychology; pertaining to forces or mental processes, such as extrasensory perception or psychokinesis, outside the possibilities defined by natural or scientific laws; as, paranormal phenomena.

parapsychology.definition: The field of study concerned with psychological phenomena not explainable by the laws of physics, especially extrasensory perception, telepathy, psychokinesis, precognition, and clairvoyance.

parasol.definition: A kind of small umbrella used by women as a protection from the sun.

parenchyma.definition: The soft cellular substance of the tissues of plants and animals, like the pulp of leaves, the soft tissue of glands, and the like.

parenchymal.definition: Of, pertaining to, or consisting of, parenchyma.

parent.definition: One who begets, or brings forth, offspring; a father or a mother.

parenthetical.definition: Of the nature of a parenthesis; pertaining to, or expressed in, or as if in, a parenthesis; as, a parenthetical clause; a parenthetic remark; a parenthetical style.

parked.definition: p. p. of park, v. t., 2; -- of vehicles; as, there were four parked cars across the street.

parking.definition: The act of maneuvering a vehicle into a location where it can be left temporarily.

parkinsonism.definition: A degenerative nervous disorder occurring mostly in persons older than 60 years, characterized in advanced stages by rhythmic muscular tremors, especially in the hands, and by rigidity of movement, a drooping posture, slow speech, and a masklike facial expression; the term designates a set of symptoms, and the underlying disease causing these symptoms is most commonly Parkinson's disease. Parkinsonism results from a deficiency in the neurotransmitter dopamine caused by degeneration of the cells producing that agent. It can be mitigated by chemotherapy with agents such as levodopa (3-hydroxy-L-tyrosine).

parkway.definition: A wide scenic road planted with trees.

parody.definition: To write a parody upon; to burlesque.

parry.definition: A warding off of a thrust or blow, as in sword and bayonet exercises or in boxing; hence, figuratively, a defensive movement in debate or other intellectual encounter.

parse.definition: To resolve into its elements, as a sentence, pointing out the several parts of speech, and their relation to each other by government or agreement; to analyze and describe grammatically.

partake.definition: To partake of; to have a part or share in; to share.

partial.definition: Of, pertaining to, or affecting, a part only; not general or universal; not total or entire; as, a partial eclipse of the moon.

participating.definition: Taking part in an activity; as, the participating organizations.

participatory.definition: Affording the opportunity for individual participation; as, participatory democracy.

particulate.definition: Matter composed of particles; -- often used in the pl.; as, the quantity of particulates in auto exhaust is strictly regulated.

partitioning.definition: An analysis into mutually exclusive categories.

parts.definition: The local environment; as, he hasn't been seen around these parts in years.

passenger.definition: A passer or passer-by; a wayfarer.

pasta.definition: Any of a variety of edible unleavened doughey preparations made from flour, eggs and water, originating in Italy, and shaped into various forms, such as solid strings (as spaghetti), hollow tubes, or layered squares (ravioli). They may be mixed with various sauces, often having a tomato base, or filled with meat or cheese fillings.

pastime.definition: To sport; to amuse one's self.

pastor.definition: A shepherd; one who has the care of flocks and herds.

patched.definition: Mended, usually clumsily by covering a hole with a patch; as, patched jeans.

patching.definition: The act of mending a hole in a garment by sewing a patch over it.

paternalistic.definition: Benevolent but sometimes intrusive; -- used often of governments and the administration of large organizations. See paternal government.

pathologist.definition: One skilled in pathology; an investigator in pathology; as, the pathologist of a hospital, whose duty it is to determine the causes of the diseases.

pathology.definition: The science which treats of diseases, their nature, causes, progress, symptoms, etc.

patina.definition: A dish or plate of metal or earthenware; a patella.

patrilineal.definition: tracing descent through the male line; as, a patrilineal society.

patrolling.definition: The activity of going around or through an area at regular intervals for security purposes.

patterned.definition: Having describable patterns, especially patterns of colors.

paved.definition: covered with a firm surface; -- of pathways or roadways.

paying.definition: yielding material gain or profit; as, paying investments.

payload.definition: The part of a missile or torpedo that carries the explosive charge.

payoff.definition: profit or gain from an action; -- used broadly; as, lots of effort with little payoff.

pct.definition: Percent; a fractional proportion, multiplied by 100.

pe.definition: The 17th letter of the Hebrew alphabet.

peacetime.definition: A period of time during which there is no war; as, civil liberties are valued more highly in peacetime than in war.

pectin.definition: One of a series of carbohydrates, commonly called vegetable jelly, found very widely distributed in the vegetable kingdom, especially in ripe fleshy fruits, as apples, cranberries, etc. It is extracted as variously colored, translucent substances, which are soluble in hot water but become viscous on cooling. It is commonly used in making fruit jelllies.

pegged.definition: Tapering toward the bottom; as, pegged pants.

penicillin.definition: Any of a variety of substances having a structure containing a beta-lactam ring fused to a thiirane ring, to which a carboxyl group is attached, but most commonly interpreted as benzyl penicillin. They are notable as powerful antibacterial agents of relatively low toxicity which have found extensive use in medicine for treating bacterial infections. They are categorized as one of the classes of beta-lactam antibiotic. They are produced naturally by some fungi and bacteria, and industrial production processes almost invariably start from some form of the penicillin nucleus produced by fermentation of microorganisms. The fermentation products are then chemically modified to produce derivatives of enhanced potency, safety, or antibacterial spectrum. The first penicillin to see extensive use clinically (during World War II) was penicillin G, also called benzypenicillin, and commonly simply PJC]

perceived.definition: Detected by instinct or inference rather than by recognized perceptual cues; as, a perceived threat.

percent.definition: A proportion multiplied by 100; as, he receives a percent of the proceeds; 3 is 75 percent of 4. Often symbolized by the character as, at 6% interest.

perceptive.definition: Of or pertaining to the act or power of perceiving; having the faculty or power of perceiving; used in perception.

perch.definition: Any fresh-water fish of the genus Perca and of several other allied genera of the family Percid, as the common American or yellow perch (Perca flavescens syn. Perca Americana), and the European perch (Perca fluviatilis).

perfected.definition: Brought into final form; completely formed; -- of plans, ideas, etc.

perfumed.definition: Filled or impregnated with perfume; as, perfumed stationery; a perfumed boudoir.

periodontitis.definition: A disease that attacks the gum and bone around the teeth.

permanent.definition: A wave or curl in the hair that lasts for months and is made durable by treating the hair with chemicals when it is curled.

permeated.definition: p. p. of permeate; as, Her poems are permeated with sorrow.

personalized.definition: Made for or directed or adjusted to a particular individual; modified for a particular person; as, personalized luggage; personalized advice.

pervasiveness.definition: The quality of filling or spreading throughout; as, the pervasiveness of the odor of cabbage in tenement hallways.

pestle.definition: To pound, pulverize, bray, or mix with a pestle, or as with a pestle; to use a pestle.

pet.definition: Petted; indulged; favorite; admired; cherished; as, a pet child; a pet lamb; a pet theory; a pet animal.

petite.definition: A size category of women's clothing, for women with less than average height.

petting.definition: Sexually titillating foreplay without contact with the genital organs.

phenotype.definition: The observable characteristics of an organism, resulting from the genetic characteristics influenced by a particular environment. Contrasted with genotype.

phobia.definition: Any irrational and persistent fear, whether of a situation, activity, or object; a phobia typically leads to a strong desire to avoid the object of the phobia.

phobic.definition: A person suffering from a phobia.

phone.definition: To get or try to get into communication with, using a telephone; as, I phoned him this morning.

phoneme.definition: One of a small set of speech sounds that are used by and distinguished by the speakers of a particular language. They are combined into morphemes, words, and sentences.

phonemic.definition: Of or pertaining to a phoneme; as, phonemic analysis.

phony.definition: Something or someone that is phony.

phylogeny.definition: The history of genealogical development; the sequence of events involved in the evolutionary development of a species or taxonomic group of organisms; the historic exolution of the phylon or tribe, in distinction from ontogeny, or the development of the individual organism, and from biogenesis, or life development generally.

physicality.definition: A preoccupation with satisfaction of physical drives and appetites; -- of people.

physiology.definition: The science which treats of the phenomena of living organisms; the study of the processes incidental to, and characteristic of, life.

physiotherapy.definition: Therapy that uses physical agents: exercise and massage and so on.

plastic.definition: A substance composed predominantly of a synthetic organic high polymer capable of being cast or molded; many varieties of plastic are used to produce articles of commerce (after 1900). [MW10 gives origin of word as 1905]

poo.definition: Excrement; feces; -- informal baby talk sometimes used as a euphemism.

premiere.definition: to perform (a play, ballet, or composition) for the first time.

prioritize.definition: To order or rank (a list of tasks) according to priority; to assign a priorities to.

promotion.definition: The act of promoting, advancing, or encouraging; the act of exalting in rank or honor; also, the condition of being advanced, encouraged, or exalted in honor; preferment.

pub.definition: A retail business where alcoholic beverages are sold by the drink; a bar; a tavern.

puzzle.definition: To perplex; to confuse; to embarrass; to put to a stand; to nonplus.

caballero.definition: A knight or cavalier; hence, a gentleman.

cacao.definition: A small evergreen tree (Theobroma Cacao) of South America and the West Indies. Its fruit contains an edible pulp, inclosing seeds about the size of an almond, from which cocoa, chocolate, and broma are prepared.

caesar.definition: A Roman emperor, as being the successor of Augustus C. Hence, a kaiser, or emperor of Germany, or any emperor or powerful ruler. See Kaiser, Kesar, Tsar.

calming.definition: tending to soothe or calm or tranquilize.

came.definition: A slender rod of cast lead, with or without grooves, used, in casements and stained-glass windows, to hold together the panes or pieces of glass.

camel.definition: A large ruminant used in Asia and Africa for carrying burdens and for riding. The camel is remarkable for its ability to go a long time without drinking. Its hoofs are small, and situated at the extremities of the toes, and the weight of the animal rests on the callous. The dromedary (Camelus dromedarius) has one hump on the back, while the Bactrian camel (Camelus Bactrianus) has two. The llama, alpaca, and vicuAuchenia).

campaigning.definition: The campaign of a candidate to be elected.

camshaft.definition: a shaft that has cams attached to it, forming part of a mechanical device.

cancerous.definition: Like a cancer; having the qualities or virulence of a cancer; affected with cancer; as, a cancerous growth.

candida.definition: any of the yeastlike imperfect fungi of the genus Candida.

candidiasis.definition: an infection caused by fungi of the genera Monilia or Candida, especially Candida albicans.

canned.definition: Recorded; in contrast with live; -- used of sound or video broadcasts.

canoe.definition: To manage a canoe, or voyage in a canoe.

canoeing.definition: The act or art of using a canoe.

canyon.definition: A deep gorge, ravine, or gulch, between high and steep banks, worn by water courses.

canonical.definition: Of or pertaining to a canon; established by, or according to, a canon or canons.

capacitance.definition: an electrical phenomenon whereby an electric charge is stored.

capacitor.definition: a device used in electronic circuits to hold electrical charge, consisting of two conducting plates separated by a nonconducting (dielectric) medium; it is characterized by its capacitance.

capital.definition: The head or uppermost member of a column, pilaster, etc. It consists generally of three parts, abacus, bell (or vase), and necking. See these terms, and Column.

capitalism.definition: An economic system based on predominantly private (individual or corporate) investment in and ownership of the means of production, distribution, and exchange of goods and wealth; contrasted with socialism or especially communism, in which the state has the predominant role in the economy.

capitalistic.definition: Of or relating to capitalism or capitalists.

capitation.definition: A numbering of heads or individuals.

captivated.definition: having an affection or admiration, caused by charm of the person or object.

carboxylic.definition: of or pertaining to the carboxyl group; having a carboxyl group (written -COOH, -CO2H or -CO.OH); as, carboxylic acids are weakly acidic.

carcinogen.definition: Any substance that produces cancer; as, to test for carcinogens in the drinking water.

carcinogenic.definition: Causing or tending to cause cancer; as, the carcinogenic action of certain chemicals or of ionizing radiation.

carcinoid.definition: A small tumor (benign or malignant) arising from the mucosa of the gastrointestinal tract; it is usually associated with excessive secretion of serotonin.

carcinoma.definition: A form of malignant cancer arising from epithelial tissue. The term was earlier applied to all forms of cancer, or to certain non-malignant forms. It is contrasted with sarcoma, a malignant form of cancer arising from connective tissue. See Cancer.

cardiovascular.definition: Of or pertaining to or involving the heart and blood vessels; as, cardiovascular conditioning.

carefree.definition: Free of trouble and worry and care; as, the carefree joys of childhood; carefree millionaires, untroubled financially.

caressing.definition: the act of embracing; holding in one's arms .

carousel.definition: a continuous belt oriented horizontally or near-horizontally around a central structure, driven in a circular motion by some mechanism, which carries luggage delivered from the luggage hold of an airplane to air travelers; -- used at airports.

carpeted.definition: covered with or as if with carpeting or with carpeting as specified; often used in combination; as, the carpeted hallway; a flower-carpeted hillside. Opposite of uncarpeted.

carved.definition: formed by carving or having a design carved into the surface.

casebook.definition: a book in which detailed written records of cases are kept and which are a source of information for subsequent work. Such books are often used as supplements to texts in law schools.

cashed.definition: converted into currency; -- of financial instruments; as, a cashed check.

cassie.definition: a type of tropical American thorny shrub or small tree (Acacia farnesiana); it bears fragrant yellow flowers used in making perfumery.

castrated.definition: deprived of reproductive organs or sexual attributes.

cat.definition: Any animal belonging to the natural family Felidae, and in particular to the various species of the genera Felis, Panthera, and Lynx. The domestic cat is Felis domestica. The European wild cat (Felis catus) is much larger than the domestic cat. In the United States the name wild cat is commonly applied to the bay lynx (Lynx rufus). The larger felines, such as the lion, tiger, leopard, and cougar, are often referred to as cats, and sometimes as big cats. See Wild cat, and Tiger cat.

catabolic.definition: Of or pertaining to catabolism; as, catabolic processes, which give rise to substances (katastates) of decreasing complexity and increasing stability.

catabolism.definition: the breakdown of more complex substances into simpler ones with release of energy, in living organisms; destructive or downward metabolism; -- a form of metabolism, opposed to anabolism. See also Disassimilation.

catalase.definition: an enzyme found in most plant and animal cells that functions as an oxidative catalyst; it decomposes hydrogen peroxide into hydrogen and water.

catalyst.definition: a substance that initiates or accelerates a chemical reaction without itself being affected; as, thousands of enzymes serve in concert as calaysts to produce the sequence of reactions we call catalyst.

catalyze.definition: to cause (a chemical reaction) to proceed more quickly by contacting the reactant(s) with another substance; as, moisture catalyzes the oxidation of iron in air.

catecholamine.definition: any of a group of chemicals including epinephrine and norepinephrine that are produced in the medulla of the adrenal gland. They function as neurotransmitters in the sympathetic nervous system. Also, any structurally related chemical substance, whether natural or synthetic.

cationic.definition: of or pertaining to cations; having a net positive charge; positively ionic; -- said of ions. Contrasted with anionic.

cecum.definition: The caecum, the cavity in which the large intestine begins and into which the ileum opens.

cedar.definition: The name of several evergreen trees. The wood is remarkable for its durability and fragrant odor.

cede.definition: To yield or surrender; to give up; to resign; as, to cede a fortress, a province, or country, to another nation, by treaty.

cellophane.definition: a transparent paper-like product made of regenerated cellulose, produced in sheets and rolls, which is impervious to moisture and germs, and which is used to wrap candy, cigarettes, and a wide variety of other products for distribution and retail sale; as, a pack of cigarettes in a cellophane wrapper.

censored.definition: suppressed or subjected to censorship; as, the censored press in some countries. Opposite of uncensored.

center.definition: A point equally distant from the extremities of a line, figure, or body, or from all parts of the circumference of a circle; the middle point or place.

centered.definition: being or placed in the center.

centralized.definition: drawn toward a center or brought under the control of a central authority; as, centralized control of emergency relief efforts; centralized government. Opposite of decentralized.

centralizing.definition: causing to concentrate at a center. Opposite of decentralizing.

centrifugation.definition: the process of separating substances by the use of a centrifuge.

centrifuge.definition: to drive out; to subject to the action of a centrifuge.

centromere.definition: a specialized condensed region of a chromosomes that appears during mitosis where the chromatids are held together to form an X shape.

certified.definition: endorsed authoritatively as having met certain requirements; guaranteed; as, certified milk; certified mail; a certified check. Opposite of uncertified.

cesium.definition: the chemical element of atomic number 55. It is a univalent element, the most electropositive metal. Symbol Cs; atomic weight 132.905. IT has a melting point of 28.4Syn. -- caesium, Cs.WordNet 1.5]

chained.definition: bound with chains; as, prisoners chained together to prevent escape.

chains.definition: metal shackles connected by chains, used to bind hands or legs; as, he was kept two weeks in chains.

chairperson.definition: the officer who presides at the meetings of an organization; -- same as chair{3} or chairman{1}, but used to achieve a sex-neutral register.

chalkboard.definition: a dark sheet of slate used as a surface for writing on, with chalk.

challenged.definition: having doubts expressed about its truth.

challenging.definition: requiring full use of one's abilities or resources; as, challenging task.

changeover.definition: an event that results in a transformation.

characterized.definition: stated precisely; -- of the meaning of words or concepts.

chased.definition: a person who is being chased; as, better to be the chaser than the chased.

chastised.definition: having bad behavior criticised and punished; as, the chastised child sat humbly in the corner.

checked.definition: Held back from some action especially by force.

checkout.definition: the latest time for vacating a hotel room without being charged for extra time; as, the checkout here is 12 noon.

checkpoint.definition: a place (as at a frontier) where travellers are stopped for inspection and clearance.

chemotherapy.definition: the use of chemical agents to treat or control disease (or mental illness); -- also used especially in reference to the use of chemicals to treat cancer.

chew.definition: To bite and grind with the teeth; to masticate.

chewing.definition: biting your food in your mouth so it becomes soft enough to swallow.

chipped.definition: having a small piece broken off; as, a chipped tooth.

chiropractic.definition: a method of medical treatment that manipulates body structures, especially the spine, in the belief that it restores proper nerve functioning.

chives.definition: A perennial plant (Allium Schoenoprasum), allied to the onion, having hollow cylindrical leaves used for seasoning. The young leaves are used in omelets, etc.

chlamydia.definition: a coccoid rickettsia which may infect birds and mammals; it causes infections of eyes and lungs and the genitourinary tract.

chlorpromazine.definition: a drug derived from phenothiazine and used as a sedative and tranquilizer.

chopsticks.definition: a pair of slender sticks made of wood, ivory, plastic, etc., used chiefly by the Chinese and Japanese to lift food into the mouth while dining; -- also commonly used around the world by persons of Oriental heritage or in restaurants serving oriental food.

chorale.definition: A stately hymn tune; a simple sacred tune, sung in unison by the congregation, used mostly in Protestant (especially Lutheran) churches; as, the Lutheran chorals.

chromatogram.definition: the paper strip, column, gel, or TLC plate on which substances have been separated by a process of chromatography{2}.

cilantro.definition: an Old World herb (Coriandrum sativum) with aromatic parsleylike leaves and seed.

cinema.definition: the art of creating motion pictures; as, this story would be good cinema; -- often used in the phrase the cinema.

circa.definition: Approximately; about; commonly abbreviated ca.; -- used especially before dates and numerical measures; as, he was born circa 1650; ca. 50 feet high.

circulating.definition: moving or flowing in a circuit and returning to the same point; as, steam circulating through the pipes; the circulating thyroid hormones.

circumstance.definition: That which attends, or relates to, or in some way affects, a fact or event; an attendant thing or state of things.

cither.definition: a musical instrument resembling a harp with strings stretch over a flat sounding box; the zither. It is played with a plectrum and with fingers.

clanging.definition: emitting a series of clangs, as of metal objects colliding.

classics.definition: the branch of learning concerned with study of the literary works of ancient Greece and Rome.

classified.definition: arranged into classes or categories; as, unclassified.

classy.definition: having elegance or taste or refinement in manners or dress. Opposite of styleless.

cleaners.definition: a shop where dry cleaning is done.

cleansed.definition: having been made clean. Opposite of dirty.

clipboard.definition: a small writing board with a clip attached at the top for holding papers.

clipped.definition: trimmed with clippers; as, a clipped hedge.

clippers.definition: a type of shears for cutting grass or shrubbery; as, hedge clippers.

clocks.definition: European weed naturalized in the southwestern U. S. and Mexico (Erodium cicutarium), having reddish decumbent stems with small fernlike leaves and small deep reddish-lavender flowers followed by slender pinlike fruits that stick straight up; it is often grown for forage.

clockwise.definition: in the same direction as the hands of a clock rotate, as viewed from in front of the clock face; -- said of that direction of a rotation about an axis, or about a point in a plane, which is ordinarily reckoned negative. Also said of the direction of a spiral, in which case the term right-handed is more common. Opposite of counterclockwise, and left-handed.

clogged.definition: obstructed so as to prevent or hinder flow of a fluid; -- of conduits; as, clogged pipes; clogged arteries.

clone.definition: to make a clone from; to make identical copies of an organism by a non-sexual process of reproduction.

clostridium.definition: spindle-shaped bacterial cell esp. one swollen at the center by an endospore.

clustered.definition: growing close together but not in dense mats; -- of plants.

coaching.definition: the job of a professional coach.

coated.definition: covered with an outer layer or film; as, sugar-coated pills.

coauthor.definition: a writer who collaborates with others in writing something.

coaxing.definition: p. pr. of coax; as, the boys' coaxing voices.

cochin.definition: an Asian breed of large fowl with dense plumage and feathered legs.

coenzyme.definition: a molecule that is essential for the activity of some enzymes; it may exist free in solution within a living organism, but functions by binding to an enzyme to assist in catalyzing a reaction. The molecule itself may be temporarily changed during the reaction, but is ultimately restored to its original form. Many vitamins function as coenzymes.

coiled.definition: curled or wound especially in concentric rings or spirals; as, a coiled snake ready to strike; the rope lay coiled on the deck. Opposite of uncoiled.

collaborate.definition: to work together with another toward a common goal, especially in an intellectual endeavor; as, four chemists collaborated on the synthesis of the compound; three authors collaborated in writing the book.

collaborative.definition: accomplished by collaboration; cooperative; as, collaborative effort of industry and the universities. Opposed to competitive.

collaborator.definition: An associate in labor, especially in literary or scientific labor.

collage.definition: any picture made by sticking together pieces of paper or photographs, especially in unusual or surprising ways.

collapsible.definition: Capable of collapsing or being collapsed; as, a collapsible boat.

colloquium.definition: A conference treating a specific topic, at which experts and specialists present their views and discuss and analyze the information presented; the emphasis on conversation among the experts and with the audience distinguishes a colloquium from the more generic conference.

colonialist.definition: a believer in or advocate of colonialism{3}.

colonic.definition: of or pertaining to the colon.

colonized.definition: inhabited by people who were born in or retain strong ties to another country.

colorful.definition: having striking color. Opposite of colorless.

colors.definition: a flag flown by a ship to show its nationality.

columnist.definition: a journalist who writes or edits a regularly scheduled column{8} in a periodical, usually in editorial style; a type of editorialist.

combo.definition: a small band of jazz musicians.

comics.definition: The section of a newspaper containing mostly comic strips; -- called also funnies and funny papers. Many but not all newspapers have a comics section.

commemorating.definition: of or pertaining to a commemoration; serving to commemorate.

commercialization.definition: the act or process of making something commercial in character. See commercialize.

commissioned.definition: holding by virtue of a commission a rank of second lieutenant or ensign or above; -- of military officers. Contrasts with noncommissioned.

committed.definition: Bound or obligated, as under a pledge to a particular cause, action, or attitude. Opposite of uncommitted.

commonality.definition: The common people; those classes and conditions of people who are below the rank of nobility; the commons.

commuting.definition: the process of travel by a commuter.

comparability.definition: a similarity allowing comparison; an approximate equivalence.

complementation.definition: the grammatical relation of a word or phrase to a predicate.

complicating.definition: the act or process of making something more complex.

compounded.definition: combined into or constituting a chemical compound.

computerized.definition: stored, processed, or analyzed by computer.

conceding.definition: the act of conceding or yielding.

concentrated.definition: Having a high density of (the indicated substance); as, a narrow thread of concentrated ore.

conceptualization.definition: the act of formulating or making a concept of something.

conceptualize.definition: to to form a concept of; as, He could not conceptualize a robot that would help paralyzed patients.

condensed.definition: representing two or more ideas or emotions by a single symbol; as, a condensed expression of various feelings and ideas.

condescending.definition: exhibiting an attitude of superiority; patronizing; -- used of behavior or attitude.

conditioner.definition: exercise that conditions the body; as, farmwork can be a good conditioner.

conditioning.definition: a learning process in which an organism's behavior becomes dependent on the occurrence of a stimulus in its environment. See conditioned response.

condo.definition: one of the units in a condominium.

condominium.definition: one of the units in a condominium{2}.

confidentiality.definition: the state or attribute of being secret; privacy; as, you must respect the confidentiality of your client's communications.

confined.definition: having movement restricted to within a certain area; -- usually a building. Opposite of unconfined.

confiscated.definition: taken without permission or consent, especially by or as if by a public authority; as, the confiscated liquor was poured down the drain; the customs agents confiscated the banned fruits.

conforming.definition: adhering to established customs or doctrines, especially in religion, as e.g. Orthodox Judaism.

conformist.definition: marked by conformity or convention; not corresponding to current customs or rules or styles; as, underneath the radical image teenagers are surprisingly conformist. Opposite of nonconformist.

confounding.definition: a mistake that results from taking one thing to be another.

confused.definition: same as confounded; as, bewildered and confused.

conjugated.definition: formed by the union of two compounds; as, a conjugated protein.

conjuring.definition: invoking a spirit or devil. See conjure, v..

connecting.definition: forming a connection; as, a connecting flight.

connote.definition: To mark along with; to suggest or indicate as additional; to designate by implication; to include in the meaning; to imply.

conserving.definition: the preservation and careful management of the environment and of natural resources.

race.definition: A game, match, etc., open only to losers in early stages of contests.

conspiratorial.definition: relating to or characteristic of conspiracy or conspirators; as, a conspiratorial whisper.

consuming.definition: taking up most of one's attention; ardent; as, politics is his consuming passion.

contemporaries.definition: all the people living at the same time or of approximately the same age.

contraception.definition: the intentional prevention of conception or impregnation, especially when accomplished by the use of contraceptive medications or devices; a form of birth control.

contraceptive.definition: a substance or device used to prevent conception.

contracting.definition: the act or process of acquiring an infectious disease; contraction; as, the contracting of a serious illness can be financially catastrophic.

conveniences.definition: things that make one comfortable and at ease.

converted.definition: spiritually reborn or converted; as, a converted sinner.

conveying.definition: the act of transferring a property title from one person to another.

cooking.definition: the practice or manner of preparing food or the food so prepared; cookery.

coolant.definition: a fluid (gas or liquid) used to cool a device by transferring heat away from one part to another.

cooled.definition: made or become cool or made cool as specified; often used as a combining form; as, air-cooled auto engine; the cooled milk was put in the refrigerator.

coordinate.definition: To make coordinate; to put in the same order or rank; as, to coordinate ideas in classification.

coordinated.definition: dexterous in the use of more than one set of muscle movements.

copied.definition: reproducing the features of an original especially in an inferior manner.

cords.definition: trousers made of corduroy cloth; corduroys.

correcting.definition: the act of offering an improvement to replace a mistake.

corroborated.definition: supported or established by evidence or proof; as, corroborated testimony is especially convincing.

corrugated.definition: shaped into parallel folds alternately grooved and ridged; as, the surface of the ocean was rippled and corrugated.

corticosteroid.definition: a steroid compound produced by the adrenal cortex, or a synthetic analog of such a compound.

corticosterone.definition: any of several steroid compounds secreted by the adrenal cortex; they are involved in regulating water and electrolyte balance in the body.

cortisol.definition: a steroid hormone (C21H30O5) active in carbohydrate and protein metabolism; -- called also hydrocortisone. It is used in medicine as an antiinflammatory agent

cortisone.definition: a corticosteroid hormone (C21H28O5) produced by the adrenal cortex. It is used in medicine as an antiinflammatory agent.

cosmology.definition: The branch of science or philosophy dealing with the origin and nature of the universe as a whole.

cottonseed.definition: The seed of the cotton plant.

counseling.definition: direction or advice as to a decision or course of action.

counterbalanced.definition: brought into equipoise by means of a weight or force that offsets another.

counterclockwise.definition: in the opposite direction to that in which the hands of a clock rotate, as viewed from in front of the clock face; -- of rotatory motion or spiral direction. Opposite of clockwise, or right-handed

counterfactual.definition: contrary to fact; -- of assertions, ideas, assumptions.

coupled.definition: joined together especially in a pair or pairs.

covariance.definition: a statistical measure of the relationship of two variables, formed by multiplying the difference of each variable from its mean, both variables being measured at the same time, and averaging all such products.

coworker.definition: One who works with another; a cooperator.

cows.definition: domesticated bovine animals as a group regardless of sex or age; as, wait till the cows come home.

cramped.definition: inconveniently small; restricting movement; -- of living quarters or workspace; as, cramped quarters; a cramped office.

crane.definition: to reach forward with head and neck, in order to see better; as, a hunter cranes forward before taking a leap.

crankcase.definition: the housing for a crankshaft and connecting parts in an internal-combustion engine.

crate.definition: To pack in a crate or case for transportation; as, to crate a sewing machine; to crate peaches.

criticize.definition: same as criticise; as, The paper criticized the new movie.

crook.definition: A bend, turn, or curve; curvature; flexure.

cropped.definition: cut very short; as, her cropped hair.

crossover.definition: the interchange of sections between pairing homologous chromosomes during the prophase of meiosis.

crowded.definition: overfilled or compacted or concentrated; filled to excess; as, a crowded program. Opposite of uncrowded.

crumbled.definition: broken into small fragments; as, crumbled cookies.

crushed.definition: treated so as to have a permanently wrinkled appearance; -- of fabrics; as, crushed velvet.

crystallize.definition: To be converted into a crystal; to take on a crystalline form, through the action of crystallogenic or cohesive attraction; to precipitate from a solution in the form of crystals.

crystallized.definition: smoothly coated with crystals of sugar; -- used especially of fruits.

cultivar.definition: a variety of a plant developed from a natural species and maintained under cultivation.

cultivated.definition: marked by refinement in taste and manners; as, cultivated tastes in art.

cum.definition: same as semen{2}; -- also spelled come.

cumbersome.definition: Burdensome or hindering, as a weight or drag; embarrassing; vexatious; cumbrous.

cunt.definition: The female pudenda; specifically the vagina.

curbed.definition: held back from some action, especially by force. Opposite of unrestrained.

curettage.definition: surgery to remove tissue or growths from a bodily cavity (as the uterus) by scraping with a curette; the act of scraping with a curette.

curtained.definition: furnished or concealed with curtains or draperies; as, a curtained alcove. Opposite of curtainless.

curved.definition: not straight; having or marked by curves. Opposite of straight.

cushioned.definition: furnished with a cushion or other device to reduce hardness.

customs.definition: money collected under a tariff; a duty imposed on imported goods.

cutaneous.definition: Of or pertaining to the skin; existing on, or affecting, the skin; as, a cutaneous disease; cutaneous absorption; cutaneous respiration; cutaneous nerves; a cutaneous infection.

cyanobacteria.definition: any of a group of photosynthetic autotrophic prokaryotic microorganisms possessing characteristics of both bacteria and plants. When classed as bacteria, they are assigned to the Cyanobacteria; when classed as plants, they are assigned to the Cyanophyta. They were earlier named blue-green algae, a term less used now in technical discussions. Since the chlorophyll within the cyanobacteria is diffused throughout the cell, rather than being contained in chloroplasts, they are no longer thought of as true plants.

cycle.definition: To cause to pass through a cycle{2}.

cyclosporine.definition: a chemical substance produced by some soil fungi, which suppresses the cellular immune response by inhibiting T cell activation, and has been used in medicine to reduce foreign tissue rejection, especially subsequent to organ transplant surgery.

cyclotron.definition: a particle accelerator that imparts energies of several million electron-volts to rapidly moving particles; it is used in investigations in nuclear physics and particle physics.

cytosine.definition: A pyrimidine (C4H5N3O) which is one of the four major basic components of DNA and RNA in most organisms, forming glyosides with ribose and deoxyribose. It is the basic component of cytidine, deoxycytidine, cytosine, cytidine monophosphate, and derivatives of those compounds.

cytoskeleton.definition: An arrangement of microtubules, microfilaments, and larger filaments within a cell serving to provide structural support of components of the cell, and to transport components from one part of the cell to another; the filaments are composed of protein and form a latticelike arrangement which may change rapidly with time.

cytosol.definition: The soluble components of the fluid matter enclosed within the cellular membrane; the portion of the cytoplasm which remains after removal of particulate components.

czar.definition: A king; a chief; the title of the emperor of Russia.

obelisk.definition: An upright, four-sided pillar, gradually tapering as it rises, and terminating in a pyramid called pyramidion. It is ordinarily monolithic. Egyptian obelisks are commonly covered with hieroglyphic writing from top to bottom.

obesity.definition: The state or quality of being obese; excessive body weight; incumbrance of flesh.

obituary.definition: That which pertains to, or is called forth by, the obit or death of a person; esp., an account of a deceased person.

obligated.definition: under a moral obligation to someone.

obliging.definition: Putting under obligation; disposed to oblige or do favors; hence, helpful; civil; kind.

obliterated.definition: destroyed so thoroughly as to be unrecognizable or imperceptible.

obscurity.definition: The quality or state of being obscure.

observed.definition: perceived with the eyes and sometimes with other senses; as, no explanation for the observed phenomena.

obsessed.definition: having or showing excessive or compulsive concern; -- used with with.

obsessive.definition: Persistently and abnormally preoccupied with some unreasonable idea.

obsidian.definition: A kind of glass produced by volcanoes. It is usually of a black color, and opaque, except in thin splinters.

occupational.definition: Of or pertaining to an occupation{3} or occupations{3}; caused by or incidental to an occupation{3}; as, occupational hazard; occupational illness.

occupied.definition: Engaged; in use; being used by a person and not free for use by someone else; as, the wc is occupied. Opposite of free, available, and unoccupied.

octagonal.definition: Having eight sides and eight angles.

octahedral.definition: Having eight faces or sides; of, pertaining to, or formed in, octahedrons; as, octahedral cleavage; an octahedral crystal.

octane.definition: Any one of a group of metametric hydrocarbons (C8H18) of the methane (paraffin) series. The most important is a colorless, volatile, inflammable liquid, found in petroleum, and a constituent of gasoline or ligroin.

octet.definition: A composition for eight parts, usually for eight solo instruments or voices.

oddity.definition: The quality or state of being odd; singularity; queerness; peculiarity; as, oddity of dress, manners, and the like.

oedema.definition: A swelling from effusion of watery fluid in the cellular tissue beneath the skin or mucous membranes; dropsy of the subcutaneous cellular tissue.

officialdom.definition: The body of all people elected or appointed to administer a government, taken collectively.

oiled.definition: Covered or treated with oil; dressed with, or soaked in, oil.

okay.definition: to approve; as, the boss okayed my proposal.

omega.definition: The last letter of the Greek alphabet. See Alpha.

omnibus.definition: Pertaining to or dealing with a variety of topics at one time; as, omnibus legislation; an omnibus budget bill.

oncoming.definition: the beginning or early stages; the onset.

ongoing.definition: Occurring at present; progressing; in progress; continuing; not past, completed, or future; as, an ongoing petition drive; an ongoing effort.

onshore.definition: coming from the sea toward the land; -- of winds and weather; as, an onshore gale. Opposed to offshore.

oo.definition: Any of several beautiful birds of the genus Moho, including the extinct Moho nobilis. They are honey-eaters native to the Hawaiian Islands. It yields the brilliant yellow feathers formerly used in making the royal robes. Called also yellow-tufted honeysucker.

opened.definition: having the covering skin pulled back; -- used of mouth or eyes; as, his mouth slightly opened. Opposite of closed.

operating.definition: pr. p. of operate; as, the operating conditions of the oxidation pond.

operational.definition: of or pertaining to operations; as, operational procedure.

operations.definition: financial transactions at a brokerage; having to do with the execution of trades and keeping customer records.

opportunistic.definition: taking immediate advantage, often unethically, of any circumstance of possible benefit; practising opportunism.

opposing.definition: characterized by active opposition; as, two bitterly opposing schools of thought.

opposite.definition: Placed over against; standing or situated over against or in front; facing; -- often with to; as, a house opposite to the Exchange; the concert hall and the state theater stood opposite each other on the plaza.

oppressed.definition: having excessive or unfair burdens imposed.

optimal.definition: Best possible; most desirable; optimum; as, the optimal concentration of a drug.

optimize.definition: To make as useful, effective, or functional as possible; as, to optimize the speed of a computer program.

optimum.definition: The most favorable condition, greatest degree, or largest amount possible under given circumstances.

orange.definition: Of or pertaining to an orange; of the color of an orange; reddish yellow; as, an orange ribbon.

orchestrated.definition: Arranged for performance by an orchestra; -- of a musical composition.

ordered.definition: having or evincing a systematic arrangement; especially, having elements succeeding in order according to rule; as, an ordered sequence; an ordered pair. Opposite of disordered or unordered.

organelle.definition: a specialized part of a cell performing a specific function, usually visible under the microscope as a distinct object; it is analogous to an organ{2}, but on a microscopic scale.

organizational.definition: Of or pertaining to organization; as, organizational structure.

organized.definition: Same as arranged; as, an organized tour.

orgasm.definition: Eager or immoderate excitement or action; the state of turgescence of any organ; erethism.

oriented.definition: Adjusted or aligned to surroundings or circumstances; sometimes used in combination; as, to get oriented on one's first day at a new job.

orienting.definition: aligning; positioning; setting into proper alignment.

ornament.definition: To adorn; to deck; to embellish; to beautify; as, to ornament a room, or a city.

ornamental.definition: Serving to ornament; characterized by ornament; beautifying; embellishing.

orthodontic.definition: Of or pertaining to orthodontics or orthodontia.

oscilloscope.definition: An electronic measuring instrument which provides a visual representation of the time variation of electrical quantities, such as voltage or current. It may be used to measure the shape of a voltage pulse or the frequency of an oscillating voltage. It can also be used to measure properties of other physical variables, such as sound or light intensity, if they can be translated into electrical voltage or current.

osmium.definition: A rare metallic element of the platinum group with atomic number 76. It is found native as an alloy in platinum ore, and in iridosmine. It is a hard, infusible, bluish or grayish white metal, and the heaviest substance known. Its tetroxide is used in histological experiments to stain tissues. Symbol Os. Atomic weight 190.2. Specific gravity 22.477.

osmosis.definition: The tendency in fluids to mix, or become equably diffused, when in contact. It was first observed between fluids of differing densities, and as taking place through a membrane or an intervening porous structure. An older term for the phenomenon was Osmose.

osmotic.definition: Pertaining to, or having the property of, osmosis; as, osmotic force.

ostracism.definition: Banishment by popular vote, -- a means adopted at Athens to rid the city of a person whose talent and influence gave umbrage.

ostrich.definition: A large bird of the genus Struthio, of which Struthio camelus of Africa is the best known species. It has long and very strong legs, adapted for rapid running; only two toes; a long neck, nearly bare of feathers; and short wings incapable of flight. The adult male is about eight feet high.

otherworldly.definition: existing outside of or not in accordance with nature.

outbreak.definition: A bursting forth; eruption; insurrection; mutiny; revolt.

outfitted.definition: furnished with essential equipment for a particular occupation or undertaking occupation; as, a well-outfitted expedition to the South Pole.

outgoing.definition: Going out; departing; leaving; as, the outgoing administration; an outgoing steamer.

outhouse.definition: A small house or building at a little distance from the main house; an outbuilding.

outlawed.definition: contrary to or forbidden by law; banned; illicit; as, a member of an outlawed political party.

outpouring.definition: An unrestrained expression (of emotion, feeling); as, an outpouring of grief over the death of Princess Diana.

outraged.definition: deeply angered at something unjust or wrong; incensed; as, a look of outraged disbelief.

outreach.definition: The act of reaching out; an effort to build connections from one person or group to another; as, the Police Department instituted a community outreach program.

outright.definition: Immediately; without delay; at once; as, he was killed outright.

over.definition: Excessively; too much or too greatly; -- chiefly used in composition; as, overwork, overhasty, overeager, overanxious, overreact, overcook.

overcast.definition: Completely or almost completely covered over with clouds; -- of the sky.

overcoat.definition: A coat worn over the other clothing; a greatcoat; a topcoat.

overdue.definition: Due and more than due; delayed beyond the proper time of arrival, payment, return, etc.; as, an overdue vessel; an overdue note; a book overdue at the library; an overdue payment.

overlapping.definition: A covering with an overlapping design, as with tiles or shingles.

overnight.definition: Occurring or accomplished during one night; as, guaranteed overnight delivery of a package.

overpowered.definition: rendered powerless especially by an excessive amount or profusion of something.

oversimplified.definition: simplified excessively so as to distort or misrepresent; -- of facts, assertions, or communications. Contrasted with overcomplicated.

overstated.definition: represented as greater than is true or reasonable; exaggerated; as, They made overstated accusations of corruption.

ovulation.definition: The formation of ova or eggs in the ovary, and the discharge of the same. In the human female the discharge occurs about halfway between menstruation times.

owned.definition: having an owner; often used in combination; as, state-owned railways. Opposite of unowned.

oxidative.definition: of or pertaining to oxidation; accompanied by oxidation.

oxidized.definition: combined with or having undergone a chemical reaction with oxygen; as, the oxidized form of iodine.

ozone.definition: A colorless gaseous substance (O3) obtained (as by the silent discharge of electricity in oxygen) as an allotropic form of oxygen, containing three atoms in the molecule. It is a strong oxidizer, and probably exists in the air, though by the ordinary tests it is liable to be confused with certain other substances, as hydrogen dioxide, or certain oxides of nitrogen. It derives its name from its peculiar odor, which resembles that of weak chlorine.

earlier.definition: occurring at a prior time; as, on earlier occasions.

earned.definition: Gained as a result of effort or action; -- used especially of income; as, earned income. Contrasted with unearned.

earner.definition: someone who earns wages in return for labor.

eased.definition: made less severe or intense; mitigated.

eaten.definition: ingested through the mouth. Contrasted with uneaten.

echoing.definition: Reflecting sounds so as to create multiple echoes; as, a hotel with echoing halls.

ecliptic.definition: A great circle of the celestial sphere, making an angle with the equinoctial of about 231913 Webster]

ecological.definition: of or pertaining to ecology; as, an ecological disaster.

ecologist.definition: a biologist who studies the relation between organisms and their environment.

ecology.definition: the branch of biology concerned with the various relations of animals and plants to one another and to their surrounding environment.

econometric.definition: of or pertaining to econometrics; as, econometric theories.

econometrics.definition: the application of mathematics and statistics to the study of economic and financial data.

economy.definition: The management of domestic affairs; the regulation and government of household matters; especially as they concern expense or disbursement; as, a careful economy.

edged.definition: having a specified kind of border or edge; as, a black-edged card; dried sweat left salt-edged patches.

edited.definition: improved or corrected by critical editing.

educate.definition: To bring up or guide the powers of, as a child; to develop and cultivate, whether physically, mentally, or morally, but more commonly limited to the mental activities or senses; to expand, strengthen, and discipline, as the mind, a faculty, etc.; to form and regulate the principles and character of; to prepare and fit for any calling or business by systematic instruction; to cultivate; to train; to instruct; as, to educate a child; to educate the eye or the taste.

efficacy.definition: Power to produce effects; operation or energy of an agent or force; production of the effect intended; as, the efficacy of medicine in counteracting disease; the efficacy of prayer.

efficiency.definition: The quality of being efficient or producing an effect or effects; efficient power; effectual agency.

efficient.definition: Causing effects; producing results; that makes the effect to be what it is; actively operative; not inactive, slack, or incapable; characterized by energetic and useful activity; as, an efficient officer, power.

ego.definition: The conscious and permanent subject of all psychical experiences, whether held to be directly known or the product of reflective thought; the subject consciously considered as non-ego.

egocentric.definition: a self-centered person with little regard for others.

elan.definition: Ardor inspired by passion or enthusiasm.

electrician.definition: An investigator of electricity; one versed in the science of electricity.

electronics.definition: the branch of physics that deals with the behavior of electrons. Electronics is primarily concerned with phenomena other than simple conduction, such as emission of electrons, storage of electrical charge, the effects of electrical fields on the conduction of electrons through a circuit, and amplification and manipulation of electric signals such as voltage or current by design of circuits. Electronics also encompasses the application of such fundamental principles to the construction of devices using the manipulation of electrons in their operation, known as electronic devices.

electrophoresis.definition: the motion of charged molecules or particles in a liquid medium under the influence of an electric field; particles with a positive charge move toward the cathode and negative to the anode.

electrophoretic.definition: of or pertaining to electrophoresis; electrophoretic mobility; accomplished using electrophoresis; as, electrophoretic separation; electrophoretic analysis.

elicited.definition: called forth from a latent or potential state by stimulation; as, an elicited response.

elite.definition: A choice or select body; the flower; as, the  of society.

elk.definition: A large deer, of several species. The European elk Alces alces (formerly Alces machlis or Cervus alces) is closely allied to the American moose. The American elk, or wapiti (Cervus Canadensis) the largest member of the deer family, has large, spreading antlers and is closely related to the European stag. See Moose, and Wapiti.

elongated.definition: having a length noticeably longer than the width.

emaciated.definition: having become so thin that the bones noticeably protrude under the skin; as, emaciated bony hands.

emancipated.definition: free from traditional social restraints; -- used especially of women; as, an emancipated young woman pursuing her career.

embarrassed.definition: feeling uneasily or unpleasantly self-conscious due to some event or circumstance; as, she was embarrassed by her child's tantrums.

embarrassing.definition: hard to deal with; as, greeted with an embarrassing silence.

embedded.definition: enclosed or fixed firmly in a surrounding mass; surrounded on all sides; as, found pebbles embedded in the silt; stone containing many embedded fossils; as, peach and plum seeds embedded in a sweet edible pulp.

emigre.definition: One of the natives of France who were opposed to the first Revolution, and who left their country in consequence.

emitting.definition: giving off light or heat or radiation; as, the physical temperature of the emitting material.

emphasis.definition: A particular stress of utterance, or force of voice, given in reading and speaking to one or more words whose signification the speaker intends to impress specially upon his audience.

emphasise.definition: To place emphasis on; same as emphasize.

emphasizing.definition: The act of giving special importance or significance to something.

emphatically.definition: With emphasis; forcibly; in a striking manner or degree; preas, he emphatically denied the allegations.

empowered.definition: invested with legal power or official authority especially as symbolized by having a scepter.

encased.definition: covered or protected with or as if with a case; as, products encased in leatherette.

enclosed.definition: surrounded or closed in, usually on all sides. Opposite of unenclosed.

enclosing.definition: the act of surrounding something with something else, so that it is inside the surrounding object.

encode.definition: To convert (a text, data) into a series of secret symbols by means of a code{5}; to encrypt.

encompassing.definition: closely enveloping or surrounding on all sides.

encouraged.definition: made to feel more courage, hope, or optimism.

encrusted.definition: covered with or hardened into a crust.

encrypt.definition: To convert ordinary language or other data into code; to hide the meaning of a message by converting it into a form that cannot be interpreted without knowing the secret method for interpretation, called the key; to encode.

encrypted.definition: converted into a coded form that cannot be interpreted without knowing the secret method for interpretation, called the key; -- of messages or other forms of information.

encryption.definition: the process of converting messages in ordinary language, or other information into a secret coded form that cannot be interpreted without knowing the secret method for interpretation, called the key.

endangered.definition: Being in a condition or situation where life or serious harm is possible; in danger; at risk.

endoscopic.definition: Of or pertaining to endoscopy or an endoscope.

endpoint.definition: A point of termination or completion.

energizing.definition: imparting or capable of imparting vitality and energy.

engrossing.definition: capable of holding the attention completely; very interesting.

enigma.definition: A dark, obscure, or inexplicable saying; a riddle; a statement, the hidden meaning of which is to be discovered or guessed.

enlightening.definition: enlightening so as to encourage intellectual or moral improvement.

enlisted.definition: designating to those members of the armed forces not commissioned as an officer; as, an enlisted man.

enlisting.definition: the act of getting recruits; convincing people to join the army, take a job, support a cause etc.

enough.definition: An exclamation denoting sufficiency, being a shortened form of it is enough.

enraged.definition: filled with or indicating extreme anger; as, an enraged bull.

ensign.definition: A flag; a banner; a standard; esp., the national flag, or a banner indicating nationality, carried by a ship or a body of soldiers; -- as distinguished from flags indicating divisions of the army, rank of naval officers, or private signals, and the like.

ensuing.definition: subsequent, or occurring as a result; as, ensuing events confirmed the prediction.

entangled.definition: in a confused mass. Contrasted with untangled.

entering.definition: incoming; -- of a person or group assuming a role. Opposite of leaving and outgoing.

entitlement.definition: a right granted by law or contract, especially to financial benefits from the government.

entrenchment.definition: an entrenched fortification; a position protected by trenches.

entrepreneurial.definition: of or pertaining to an entrepreneur or entrepreneurship; as, entrepreneurial risks.

entrepreneurship.definition: the activity of organizing, managing, and assuming the risks of a business enterprise.

enveloped.definition: enclosed or surrounded completely; as, the fog-enveloped city.

enveloping.definition: the act or process of enclosing something inside something else.

environmental.definition: of or pertaining to the environment; as, environmental factors.

enzyme.definition: A protein produced by a living organism, capable of catalyzing a chemical reaction. Almost all processes in living organisms require some form of enzyme to cause the reactions to occur at a rate sufficient to support life. There are a very wide variety of enzymes, each specifically catalyzing a different chemical reaction, the sum of which cause the bulk of the physiological changes observed as life processes. Enzymes, like most proteins, are synthesized by the protein-synthetic mechanism of the living cell, at special sites on ribosomes, using the genetic information in messenger RNA transcribed from the genetic instructions stored as nucleotide sequences in the DNA (or in some viruses, the RNA) of the genome. Some examples of enzymes are: pepsin, diastase, rennet, DNA polymerase, invertase, glucose oxidase, protease, and ribonuclease. There are many other types of enzyme.

epidemiological.definition: Connected with, or pertaining to, epidemiology; as, epidemiological studies.

epidemiology.definition: That branch of medicine which studies the incidence and distribution of disease in a population, and uses such information to find the causes, modes of transmission, and methods for control of disease.

epistemological.definition: of or pertaining to epistemology; as, epistemic modal.

epistemology.definition: The theory or science of the method or grounds of knowledge.

equating.definition: the act of regarding as equal.

erecting.definition: the act of building or putting up.

ergonomics.definition: biological science applied to study the relation between workers and their environments.

erudite.definition: Characterized by extensive reading or knowledge; well instructed; learned.

erudition.definition: The act of instructing; the result of thorough instruction; the state of being erudite or learned; the acquisitions gained by extensive reading or study; particularly, learning in literature or criticism, as distinct from the sciences; scholarship.

erupt.definition: To eject something, esp. lava, water, etc., as a volcano or geyser; as, when Mount Saint Helens erupted, some people were taken by surprise.

eruption.definition: The act of breaking out or bursting forth;

established.definition: brought about or set up or accepted; especially long and widely accepted; as, distrust of established authority; a team established as a member of a major league; enjoyed his prestige as an established writer; an established precedent; the established Church. Contrasted with unestablished.

estimated.definition: calculated approximately; as, an estimated mass of 25 g.

etched.definition: Cut or impressed into a surface.

ethane.definition: A gaseous hydrocarbon, C2H6, forming a constituent of ordinary illuminating gas. It is the second member of the paraffin series, and its most important derivatives are common alcohol (ethyl alcohol), acetaldehyde, ether, and acetic acid. Called also dimethyl.

ethanol.definition: The organic compound C2H5.OH, the common alcohol which is the intoxicating agent in beer, wine, and other fermented and distilled liquors; called also ethyl alcohol. It is used pure or denatured as a solvent or in medicines and colognes and cleaning solutions, or mixed in gasoline as a fuel for automobiles, and as a rocket fuel (as in the V-2 rocket).

ethic.definition: the principles of right and wrong that are accepted by an individual or a social group; as, the Puritan ethic.

ethnocentric.definition: centered on a specific ethnic group, usually one's own; exhibiting ethnocentrism (in both senses).

ethnocentrism.definition: belief in the superiority of one's own ethnic group.

etude.definition: A composition in the fine arts which is intended, or may serve, for a study.

eukaryotic.definition: having cells with visible nuclei surrounded by a nuclear membrane; pertaining to eukaryotes. Contrasted with prokaryotic.

euphoria.definition: a strong pleasant feeling of well-being or happiness; it is often caused by attainment of a desired goal or other incident of accomplishment, but may irrationally accompany a pathological manic state.

euphoric.definition: strongly experiencing a feeling of well-being; feeling euphoria. Opposite of dysphoric.

eutectic.definition: a mixture of substances having a composition providing the minimum melting point for mixtures of those substances. Called also a eutectic mixture.

evaluative.definition: exercising or involving careful analytical evaluations.

evaluator.definition: an authority who is able to estimate worth or quality; an appraiser.

evangelism.definition: The preaching or promulgation of the gospel.

evangelist.definition: A bringer of the glad tidings of Church and his doctrines.

evaporated.definition: reduced in volume by having moisture expelled before canning; same as condensed, 3; as, unsweetened evaporated milk.

evasion.definition: The act of eluding or avoiding, particularly the pressure of an argument, accusation, charge, or interrogation; artful means of eluding.

evasive.definition: Tending to evade, or marked by evasion; elusive; shuffling; avoiding by artifice.

ex.definition: Without (some right); not including the right to have; as, a stock selling ex dividend (a stock for which the right to a dividend has expired the previous day); ex interest; ex rights.

exchange.definition: The act of giving or taking one thing in return for another which is regarded as an equivalent; as, an exchange of cattle for grain.

executing.definition: putting a condemned person to death.

exercisable.definition: That may be exercised, used, or exerted; as, the stock options are exercisable for only five years from the date of issue.

exhilarated.definition: elated, in high spirits, and envigorated. Opposite of dejected.

existentialism.definition: a philosophical theory or attitude having various interpretations, generally emphasising the existence of the individual as a unique agent with free will and responsibility for his or her own acts, though living in a universe devoid of any certain knowledge of right and wrong; from one's plight as a free agent with uncertain guidelines may arise feelings of anguish. Existentialism is concerned more with concrete existence rather than abstract theories of essences; is contrasted with rationalism and empiricism; and is associated with Kierkegaard, Heidegger and Sartre, as well as others.

existing.definition: having existence or being or actuality; as, much of the beluga caviar existing in the world is found in the Soviet Union and Iran. Opposite of nonexistent.

exogenous.definition: derived from or originating outside; pertaining to, or having the character of, an exogen; -- the opposite of endogenous.

expanded.definition: increased in extent or size or bulk or scope. Opposite of contracted.

expelling.definition: any of several bodily processes by which substances go out of the body.

expended.definition: nonexistent or unavailable as a consequence of use or exchange.

experienced.definition: Taught by practice or by repeated observations; skillful or wise by means of trials, use, or observation; as, an experienced physician, workman, soldier; an experienced eye.

expired.definition: having come to an end or become void after passage of a period of time; as, an expired passport; caught driving with an expired license. Opposite of unexpired.

exposed.definition: with no protection or shield; as, the exposed northeast frontier.

expressionism.definition: an art movement early in the 20th century; the artist's subjective expression of inner experiences was emphasized.

expressionist.definition: an artist who is an adherent of expressionism.

expropriated.definition: taken out of the possession of another and transferred to one's own use often without permission; as, the expropriated land was developed into a public playground.

extinguished.definition: caused to die out because of the absence or withdrawal of reinforcement; -- of a conditioned response.

extracellular.definition: located or occurring outside of a living cell or cells; as, extracellular fluid. Opposite of intracellular.

extraterrestrial.definition: a hypothetical form of life existing outside the Earth or its atmosphere, especially intelligent life on other planets or in other solar systems; as, what would you say to an extraterrestrial?.

eyebrow.definition: The brow or hairy arch above the eye.

eyeglasses.definition: a pair of lenses fixed together in a frame, used for correcting defective vision. Also called a pair of eyeglasses. See also eyeglass{1}.

ka.definition: A spiritual aspect of the individual, living within the body during life, and surviving the body after death. It was believed to be one of two spirits inhabiting the body, the other being the ba, which deserts teh body at death.

kangaroo.definition: Any one of numerous species of jumping marsupials of the family Macropodid. They inhabit Australia, New Guinea, and adjacent islands, They have long and strong hind legs and a large tail, while the fore legs are comparatively short and feeble. The giant kangaroo (Macropus major) is the largest species, sometimes becoming twelve or fourteen feet in total length. The tree kangaroos, belonging to the genus Dendrolagus, live in trees; the rock kangaroos, of the genus Petrogale, inhabit rocky situations; and the brush kangaroos, of the genus Halmaturus, inhabit wooded districts. See Wallaby.

karate.definition: a traditional Japanese system of unarmed combat; sharp blows and kicks are given to pressure-sensitive points on the body of the opponent.

keratin.definition: A sulfur-containing fibrous protein constituting the main structural protein of hard epidermal tissues, such as horn, hair, feathers, nails, claws, hoofs, and the like. It is an insoluble substance, and, unlike elastin, is not dissolved even by gastric or pancreatic juice. By decomposition with sulphuric acid it yields leucine and tyrosine plus various other acid-stable amino acids. The amino acid composition varies, but it usually has a high percentage of cystine, which stabilizes and insolubilizes the protein by forming intrachain linkages. A softer form of keratin is present in the epidermis and whalebone. Called also epidermose.

ketchup.definition: A pureed table sauce made predominantly from tomatoes, flavored with onions, sugar, salt and spices; called also tomato ketchup. The term is also applied to pureed sauces containing mushrooms, walnuts, etc., being called in such cases mushroom ketchup, walnut ketchup, etc.

key.definition: Essential; most important; as, the key fact in the inquiry; the president was the key player in the negotiations.

keyword.definition: A word used as an entry point into an index which serves to identify files, records, texts, or other data containing the keyword or some related word, such as a synonym. It is a type of key{15}; as, a boolean combination of keywords is more effective for information retrieval than a single key{15}.

kibbutz.definition: an Israeli communal{2} form of agricultural settlement. Originally it was predominantly agricultural and practiced a very high level of sharing, including collective rearing of children. More recently (by 1998) industries have taken over a significant role in the Kibbutz economy, and the level of sharing has dropped significantly.

kicking.definition: The act of delivering a blow with the foot.

kidnapping.definition: the unlawful act of capturing and carrying away a person against their will and holding them in false imprisonment.

killing.definition: The act or process of causing a living organism to die.

kimono.definition: A kind of loose robe or gown tied with a sash, worn as a traditional outer garment by Japanese women and men. Women may wear it with a broad sash called an obi, having a large bow in the back. At present (1998), most Japanese wear it only at home or on ceremonial occasions, western-style clothing being more common in the workplace.

kinase.definition: One of a class of enzymes that catalyze transfer of a phosphate group from ATP to another molecule; it is a type of phosphorylase.

kinetic.definition: Moving or causing motion; motory; active, as opposed to latent.

knead.definition: To perform movements like kneading, with the paws; -- said of cats, which may knead{3} a master's body when stroked, presumably a sign of contentment; as, a cat kneading and purring in his master's lap.

knowledgeable.definition: thoroughly acquainted with and skilled in something through study or experience; as, knowledgeable in classical languages. Opposite of unversed, unacquainted, and unfamiliar.

knuckles.definition: a small metal weapon, worn over the knuckles on the back of the hand; called also brass knuckles and knuckle duster.

kolkhoz.definition: A collective farm owned by the communist state, in the former USSR.

aas.definition: a loose sleeveless outer garment made from aba cloth; worn by Arabs.
