ical.definition: Of or pertaining to the Brahmans or to their doctrines and worship.

abridged.definition: shortened by condensing or rewriting; -- said of texts

abs.definition: The abductor muscles of the stomach; -- a contraction used by body-building and health enthusiasts. Used similarly to pecs and delts.

acacia.definition: A genus of leguminous trees and shrubs. Nearly 300 species are Australian or Polynesian, and have terete or vertically compressed leaf stalks, instead of the bipinnate leaves of the much fewer species of America, Africa, etc. Very few are found in temperate climates.

accented.definition: having the main stress of a word; -- used of syllables

accumulated.definition: brought together into a group or crowd

ace.definition: to get a grade of "A"; as, to ace an exam.

acetaminophen.definition: a white crystalline compound (HO.C6H4.NH.CO.CH3) used as an analgesic and also as an antipyretic. It has molecular weight 151.16. It is the active ingredient in the commercial analgesics Tylenol and Datril.

acetone.definition: A volatile liquid (CH3.CO.CH3); pyroacetic spirit; methyl ketone; -- obtained by fermentation, the distillation of certain acetates, or by the destructive distillation of citric acid, starch, sugar, or gum, with quicklime. It is commonly used as a solvent.

acetylcholine.definition: a neurotransmitter released by the transmitting dendron at autonomous synapses and at neuromuscular junctions. It is a quaternary amine with an obligatory negative counterion. The nominal formula for the hydroxide form is C7H17NO3. Structural formula (CH3)3N(+)CH2CH2.O.CO.CH3.OH(-).

acetylcholinesterase.definition: an enzyme which exists in nerve cells and hydrolyses acetylcholine into choline and acetic acid.

acidosis.definition: abnormally high acidity of the blood and other body fluids.

acknowledge.definition: To own or admit the knowledge of; to recognize as a fact or truth; to declare one's belief in; as, to acknowledge the being of a God.

acknowledged.definition: Generally accepted or recognized as correct or reasonable. Opposite of unacknowledged.

acme.definition: The top or highest point; the culmination.

acne.definition: Inflammation of the sebaceous glands that are associated with hair follicles, leading to visible comedones and pimples, especially on the face, back, and chest.

acquired.definition: gotten through environmental forces. Contrasted with inherited.

acrylic.definition: Of or containing acryl, the hypothetical radical (R.CH:CH.CO-) of which acrolein (H2C:CH.CHO) is the hydride; as, acrylic acid. The characteristic residue in an acrylic compound is the carbonyl group attached directly to an ethylenic carbon.

acrylonitrile.definition: a colorless liquid compound (H2C:CH.CN); used as raw material for acrylic fibers, and as a solvent.

activated.definition: treated with aeration and bacteria to aid decomposition; -- of sewage

activator.definition: any agency bringing about activation; (Biol.) a molecule that increases the activity of an enzyme or a protein that increases the production of a gene product in DNA transcription.

activism.definition: a policy of taking direct and militant action to achieve a political or social goal.

activist.definition: one who is aggressively active on behalf of a cause.

actualized.definition: changed from potential to actual; as, saw his worst fears actualized.

addressed.definition: marked with a destination; -- of mail

adenoma.definition: A benign tumor of epithelial tissue with a glandlike structure.

adore.definition: To worship with profound reverence; to pay divine honors to; to honor as a deity or as divine.

adoring.definition: feeling or showing profound respect or veneration. Opposite of irreverent.

adrenergic.definition: producing or activated by epinephrine or adrenaline

adrenocortical.definition: of or pertaining to the adrenal cortex.

adsorption.definition: the process by which molecules of a substance form a thin film on the surface of a solid. Distinguished from absorption, in which the foreign substance penetrates the body of the absorbing material.

adulterated.definition: having been made impure by addition of inferior ingredients; -- said of substances or foods

advertising.definition: a communication publicly promoting some product or service.

advised.definition: Carefully thought out; likely to be the best course; -- said of actions. Often used in combination; as, ill-advised, well-advised.

aegis.definition: A shield or protective armor; -- applied in mythology to the shield of Jupiter which he gave to Minerva. Also fig.: A shield; a protection.

aerated.definition: treated by having air passed or bubbled through it for purification; -- of a liquid

aerial.definition: a pass to a receiver downfield from the passer.

aeroplane.definition: A light rigid plane used in aairfoil.

aerospace.definition: of or pertaining to aerospace in either sense.

aetiology.definition: The science, doctrine, or demonstration of causes; esp., the investigation of the causes of any disease; the science of the origin and development of things; etiology.

affection.definition: The act of affecting or acting upon; the state of being affected.

agency.definition: The faculty of acting or of exerting power; the state of being in action; action; instrumentality.

agenda.definition: a temporally organized plan for matters to be attended to.

aggravated.definition: made more severe or intense, especially in law; as, aggravated assault.

agitated.definition: troubled emotionally and usually deeply. Opposite of unagitated.

agitating.definition: causing or tending to cause anger or resentment.

agreeing.definition: in agreement; of the same mind; having the same opinion.

ailing.definition: sick; unhealthy. Opposite of well or healthy.

ain.definition: belonging to or on behalf of a specified person especially one's self; preceded by a possessive.

airborne.definition: conveyed by or through air, as dust or pollen; as, a clean room is needed to avoid airborne contaminants.

airfield.definition: a place where planes take off and land; an airport; -- usually used of airports other than those with regularly scheduled commercial flights, such as those at military bases or small fields for private aircraft.

airfoil.definition: a surface such as the wing of an airplane designed to provide reactive force when in motion relative to the surrounding air.

airline.definition: an organization, usually commercial or governmental, providing transportation by airplane for freight or passengers. The term includes the organization, its personnel, equipment and other properties, such as approved air routes.

airplane.definition: a heavier-than-air aircraft. Same as aeroplane{2}.

airspace.definition: the atmosphere above a nation and deemed to be under its jurisdiction.

airstrip.definition: an airfield without normal airport facilities.

airwaves.definition: the medium of transmission of signals by radio or television stations; by radio transmission; -- used non-technically; as, over the airwaves, i. e. by radio or television.

airway.definition: a duct that provides ventilation, as in mines.

alcoholism.definition: Chronic excessive drinking of alcoholic beverages that leads to social, occupational, psychological and physiological problems.

alerting.definition: a state of readiness to respond.

algorithm.definition: a precise rule (or set of rules) specifying how to solve some problem; a set of procedures guaranteed to find the solution to a problem.

algorithmic.definition: of or pertaining to an algorithm.

aligned.definition: in or brought into line with or into proper relative position; -- of spatial position.

alkalosis.definition: abnormally high alkalinity in the blood and other body fluids.

allele.definition: one of two or more alternative forms of a gene that can have the same place on homologous chromosomes and are responsible for alternative traits.

alligator.definition: to form shallow cracks in a reticulated pattern on the surface, or in a coating on the surface, of an object.

altogether.definition: nakedness; -- used mostly in the phrase altogether [informal]Syn. -- raw, buff, birthday suitWordNet 1.5]

ambivalent.definition: undecided as to whether or not to take a proposed course of action; having feelings both for and against the proposed action.

amenities.definition: things that make you comfortable and at ease.

ammonia.definition: A gaseous compound of hydrogen and nitrogen, NH3, with a pungent smell and taste: -- often called volatile alkali, and spirits of hartshorn. It is very soluble in water, forming a moderately alkaline solution, and is used in aqueous solution as a household cleaning agent, such as for cleaning grease from glass.

amnesty.definition: Forgetfulness; cessation of remembrance of wrong; oblivion.

ampicillin.definition: a semisynthetic penicillin which can be considered as the common benzylpenicillin containing an amino group at the alpha benzyl position.

amyloidosis.definition: A disorder characterized by deposit of extracellular amyloid{2} in organs or tissues in an amount that interferes with normal function of the affected organ; it is often secondary to chronic rheumatoid arthritis or tuberculosis or multiple myeloma. Called also amyloid degeneration waxy degeneration and lardaceous degeneration.

ana.definition: Of each; an equal quantity; as, wine and honey, ana (or, contracted, aa) two ounces, , that is, of wine and honey, each, two ounces.

anaesthesia.definition: Entire or partial loss or absence of feeling or sensation; a state of general or local insensibility produced by disease or by the inhalation or application of an anaesthetic.

anaesthetic.definition: A substance which produces anesthesia, as chloroform, ether, etc.

analgesic.definition: a medication which serves to reduce the sensibility to pain without loss of consciousness. Aspirin and acetaminophen (paracetamol, trade name Tylenol) are commonly used non-prescription analgesics.

anaphora.definition: A repetition of a word or of words at the beginning of two or more successive clauses.

anaphoric.definition: Of or pertaining to anaphora; as, anaphoric reference.

anaphylactic.definition: Of or pertaining to anaphylaxis; caused by anaphylaxis.

anaphylaxis.definition: Hypersensitivity (to a foreign antigen) resulting from prior contact with the same or a related substance.

androgen.definition: a hormone, such as testosterone or androsterone, that promotes development and maintenance of typical male sexual characteristics. They are mostly produced in the testes.

anesthetized.definition: rendered insensible by anesthetizing. Same as anaesthetized.

anew.definition: Over again; another time; in a new form; afresh; as, to arm anew; to create anew.

angina.definition: Any inflammatory affection of the throat, as the quinsy, malignant sore throat, croup, etc., especially such as tends to produce suffocation, choking, or shortness of breath.

anguished.definition: suffering anguish; experiencing extreme pain, distress, or anxiety

anionic.definition: a class of synthetic detergents in which the molecules do not ionize in aqueous solutions.

announced.definition: stated publicly; as, their announced intentions.

annoyed.definition: aroused to impatience or anger; as, feeling annoyed by the constant teasing.

another.definition: One more, in addition to a former number; a second or additional one, similar in likeness or in effect.

anoxia.definition: A physiological state in which insufficient oxygen reaches the tissues of the body, especially when of sufficient severity to cause permanent damage; severe hypoxia.

anoxic.definition: Of, pertaining to, or suffering from, anoxia.

antagonism.definition: Opposition of action; counteraction or contrariety of things or principles.

antagonist.definition: One who contends with another, especially in combat; an adversary; an opponent.

antagonists.definition: muscles having opposite effects; the contraction of one neutralizes the contraction of the other.

antebellum.definition: belonging to a period before a war, especially the American Civil War.

antibiotic.definition: of or pertaining to an antibiotic.

anticipated.definition: expected; opposite of unanticipated and unexpected.

antitrust.definition: opposed to trusts, monopolies, or other large combinations of business or capital which threaten fair competition; designed to protect trade and commerce from unfair business practices; -- of laws and regulations.

apartheid.definition: segregation by race; -- a term used in South Africa.

appalled.definition: struck with fear, dread, or consternation.

appointed.definition: having acquired an office or responsibility through appointment; -- said of officials, and contrasting with elected.

appropriated.definition: taken without permission or consent especially by public authority.

appurtenances.definition: miscellaneous articles needed for a particular operation or sport etc.

apraxia.definition: inability to make purposeful movements, but without paralysis or loss of sensory function.

aquaculture.definition: the cultivation of aquatic animals, such as fish or shellfish, or of plants, such as seaweed, in a controlled and sometimes enclosed body of water. The term includes use of either salt or fresh water. It is a form of agriculture, but under water.

aquifer.definition: an underground bed or layer yielding ground water for wells and springs etc.; as, the Oglala aquifer. The water contained in an aquifer may be of great age, and in such cases is sometimes called fossil water.

arb.definition: Someone who engages in arbitrage (who purchases securities in one market for immediate resale in another in the hope of profiting from the price differential); shortened form of arbitrageur.

archives.definition: a collection of records especially about an institution.

armoured.definition: provided with protective covering; -- used of animals. Opposite of unarmored.

arranged.definition: disposed or placed in a particular kind of order.

arranging.definition: the act of arranging a piece of music.

arriving.definition: directed or moving inward or toward a center; as, arriving trains.

arteriovenous.definition: connecting an artery to a vein.

artwork.definition: photographs, illustrations, or other visual representations other than the text, in a printed publication.

as.definition: Denoting equality or likeness in kind, degree, or manner; like; similar to; in the same manner with or in which; in accordance with; in proportion to; to the extent or degree in which or to which; equally; no less than; as, ye shall be as gods, knowing good and evil; you will reap as you sow; do as you are bidden.

assembled.definition: brought together into a group or crowd.

assimilating.definition: tending to or characterized by or causing assimilation (being absorbed into or incorporated).

astounded.definition: struck with an intense and usually sudden surprise sufficient to produce wonder or perplexity

astronaut.definition: a person trained to travel in a spacecraft; one who travels in a spacecraft; -- called in the Soviet Union and Russia cosmonaut.

astrophysics.definition: the concerned with the physical and chemical properties of celestial bodies.

atherosclerosis.definition: a form of arteriosclerosis characterized by irregular fatty deposits on the inner surface of large and medium-sized arteries; the deposits are associated with fibrosis and calcification of the inner layer of the arteries. Similar conditions may be found in swine and fowl. The deposits may become large enough to impede the blood circulation and in some cases may restrict the blood supply to the heart.

atrioventricular.definition: relating to or affecting the atria and ventricles of the heart.

attentiveness.definition: the quality of paying careful attention; attentiveness to detail.

audio.definition: the part of a transmitted signal which conveys the sound of the event represented by the signal, such as that of a television program.

audiovisual.definition: materials using sight or sound to present information; -- usually used in the plural.

austenite.definition: a solid solution of ferric carbide or carbon in iron; -- it cools to form pearlite or martensite.

authentication.definition: a mark on an article of trade to indicate its origin and authenticity.

authorise.definition: grant authorization or clearance for. Same as authorize.

authorities.definition: the organization that is the governing authority of a political unit.

autism.definition: a mental disorder characterized by inability to engage in normal social interactions and intense self-absorption, and usually accompanied by other symptoms such as language dysfunctions and repetitive behavior.

auto.definition: of or pertaining to an automobile; as, an auto mechanic.

automate.definition: make automatic; to change [a process] so that it is mostly automatic; to substitute machinery for human labor in an activity.

automated.definition: accomplished by machinary without the intervention of a human operator; -- of processes.

automotive.definition: of or pertaining to the automobile.

auxin.definition: a substance which, in small concentrations, promotes root formation, bud growth, or certain other processes such as fruit ripening or leaf drop in plants.

awareness.definition: conscious knowledge; as, he had no awareness of his mistakes.

awash.definition: Washed by the waves or tide; -- said of a rock or strip of shore;

bacilli.definition: plural of bacillus; usually designating aerobic rod-shaped spore-producing bacteria; they often occur in chainlike formations.

backache.definition: an ache localized in the back.

backdrop.definition: the scenery hung at back of stage. Also called in Britain backcloth.

backpack.definition: to hike while carrying a backpack; -- often used in the form go backpacking; as, to backpack through the forest.

backstage.definition: concealed from the public; in private.

backup.definition: anything kept in reserve to serve as a substitute in case of failure or unavailability of the normal or primary object; -- used for devices, plans, people, etc. Also used attributively; as, there was no backup for the electrical supply; a backup motor; a backup generator.

bacteremia.definition: The presence of bacteria in the blood.

bacteriophage.definition: a virus which infects bacteria; -- also colloquially called phage in laboratory jargon.

baggage.definition: The clothes, tents, utensils, and provisions of an army.

baiting.definition: harassment, especially of a tethered animal.

baked.definition: dried out by heat or excessive exposure to sunlight.

balanced.definition: being in a state of proper balance or equilibrium; -- opposite of unbalanced.

bam.definition: An imposition; a cheat; a hoax.

banding.definition: A strip or stripe of a contrasting color or material.

bandura.definition: A traditional Ukrainian stringed musical instrument shaped like a lute, having many strings.

bandwagon.definition: A popular trend that attracts growing support.

bandwidth.definition: The maximum rate of information transfer (measured in bits/second) that can be carried by a communication channel.

banjo.definition: A stringed musical instrument having a head and neck like the guitar, and a circular body like a tambourine. It has five strings, and is played with the fingers and hands.

barring.definition: the act of excluding someone by a negative vote or veto.

baseline.definition: an imaginary line or standard by which things are measured or compared; as, they established a baseline for the budget.

basics.definition: a statement of fundamental facts or principles.

bathtub.definition: A relatively large tub used to take a bath, usually a permanent fixture in a bathroom; it is an open container that is filled with water, in which a person immerses himself for the purpose of washing the body.

battered.definition: In deplorable condition; as, the battered old Ford station wagon.

battering.definition: the act or process of subjecting to strong repeated blows.

battlefield.definition: a region where a battle is fought.

battleground.definition: a region where a battle is fought; same as battlefield.

battleship.definition: An armor-plated warship built of steel and heavily armed, generally having over ten thousand tons displacement, and intended to be fit to combat the heaviest enemy ships in line of battle; the most heavily armed and armored class of warship at any given time.

baud.definition: A unit of transmission speed for information conveyed over a digital communications channel, usually taken as equal to the number of bits of information transmitted per second. The speed in bauds indicates the number of signalling events per second; however, since it is necessary in most cases to transmit control information along with the data, the data signalling rate may be smaller than the baud rate.

beachhead.definition: an area in hostile territory that has been occupied and is held to allow additional troops and supplies to enter.

beaded.definition: imp. & p. p. of bead, v. t. & i..

behaviorism.definition: an approach to psychology that emphasizes observable measurable behavior.

behaviorist.definition: a psychologist who subscribes to behaviorism.

bentonite.definition: An absorbent aluminum silicate clay formed from volcanic ash.

bereaved.definition: mourning due to the death of a loved one.

beret.definition: a cap made of soft cloth with no brim or bill, widening somewhat outward from a close-fitting headband to a flat top, which often has a button or tab in its center.

beth.definition: the 2nd letter of the Hebrew alphabet.

bimodal.definition: having or occurring with two modes{9}; having two maxima; -- of a curve or distribution.

bimonthly.definition: Occurring, done, or coming, once in two months; as, bimonthly visits; bimonthly publications.

bingo.definition: a game commonly used for low-stakes gambling, in which numbered balls or slips are drawn at random and players cover the corresponding numbers on their cards, called Bingo cards, which have square arrangement of such numbers. Each card has a different arrangement of the numbers, and the first player to cover all numbers in one row (horizontal, vertical, or diagonal) is the winner, usually announcing that fact by a cry of  Variants of the game may require that all peripheral numbers are covered, to form a box, or other figure. The numbers usually have one letter from the group Syn. -- lotto, beano, keno.WordNet 1.5]

biochemical.definition: a chemical substance produced by a living organism, or such a substance produced synthetically.

biofeedback.definition: a training program in which a person is given information about physiological processes (heart rate or blood pressure) that is not normally available with the goal of gaining conscious control of them.

biogenic.definition: produced by living organisms; as, biogenic methane.

biomedical.definition: Pertaining to the biological and physiological aspects of medicine.

biosynthesis.definition: production of a chemical compound by a living organism.

biota.definition: all the plant and animal life of a particular region.

biotin.definition: a B vitamin (C10H16N2O3S) that aids in body growth; -- called also vitamin H and coenzyme R. It functions as a coenzyme in many carboxylation reactions.

birthrate.definition: the ratio of live births in an area to the population of that area; usually expressed as births per 1000 population per year.

bistro.definition: a small informal restaurant, especially one serving alcoholic beverages.

blackout.definition: a suspension of radio or tv broadcasting.

blaring.definition: harshly or unpleasantly loud (in sound intensity); -- used mostly of electronic entertainment devices, such as TV, radio, or phonograph.

blended.definition: combined or mixed together so that the constituent parts are indistinguishable. Antonym of unblended.

blinded.definition: deprived of one's sight; rendered blind.

blindfold.definition: a flexible object placed over the eyes to prevent seeing; usually a strip of cloth wrapped around the head so as to cover the eyes.

blindfolded.definition: having a blindfold placed over the eyes; -- done to prevent the wearer from seeing.

blistering.definition: harshly or corrosively critical in tone; -- of comments about people or their actions.

blitz.definition: a quick move by defensive players toward the passer on the offensive team, as soon as the ball is snapped; -- it is used when the defensive teams assumes that a pass will be attempted, and risks allowing substantial gains by the offensive team if other plays are in fact planned.

blossoming.definition: the process of budding and unfolding of blossoms.

blues.definition: a type of folk song that originated among Black Americans at the beginning of the 20th century; has a melancholy sound from repeated used of blue notes.

blurred.definition: out of focus; not sharply defined.

boardinghouse.definition: a private house that provides accommodations and meals for paying guests.

boardroom.definition: a room where a committee meets (such as the board of directors of a company).

boards.definition: the boarding that surrounds an ice hockey rink.

boardwalk.definition: a walkway made of wooden boards; usually at a seaside. The more elaborate boardwalks at shore resorts are lined with many commercial retail establishments, on the side of the walk opposite the ocean.

bolshevism.definition: a form of communism based on the writings of Marx and Lenin.

bomber.definition: a military aircraft that drops bombs during flight.

bonding.definition: the process of fastening firmly together.

boo.definition: to show displeasure (after a performance or speech) by making a prolonged sound of WordNet 1.5]

boogie.definition: To do a lively dance, often with the two partners not touching, to the accompaniment of rock music.

bop.definition: an early form of modern jazz (originating around 1940).

bordered.definition: having a border especially of a specified kind; sometimes used as a combining term; as, black-bordered handkerchief. Antonym of unbordered.

bored.definition: tired of the world; bored with life.

bosom.definition: To inclose or carry in the bosom; to keep with care; to take to heart; to cherish.

bottleneck.definition: to become narrower as one approaches a point; -- said of roads; as, right by the bridge, the road bottlenecks.

bounded.definition: having the limits or boundaries established.

bounds.definition: the line or plane indicating the limit or extent of something; as, the football was caught out of bounds.

bowed.definition: bent over; -- used of back or head.

boxed.definition: enclosed in or set off by a border or box; as, boxed sections of the report; boxed announcements in the newspaper.

braced.definition: held up by braces or buttresses.

bradykinin.definition: a hypotensive tissue hormone (C50H73N15O11) which acts on smooth muscle, dilates peripheral vessels and increases capillary permeability. It is formed locally in injured tissue and is believed to play a role in the inflammatory process. It is a nonapeptide with the sequence: Arg-Pro-Pro-Gly-Phe-Ser-Pro-Phe-Arg.

braided.definition: adorned with braid; as, his braided collar.

brainstorm.definition: to try to solve a problem by discussing it exhaustively in an intense group meeting encouraging uninhibited and spontaneous contributions from all members.

brainwashing.definition: the process of forcible indoctrination into a new set of attitudes and beliefs.

brakes.definition: the combination of interacting parts that work to slow a moving vehicle.

branched.definition: resembling a fork; divided or separated into two branches; as, long branched hairs on its legs, on which pollen collects.

briefcase.definition: a small suitcase with a handle; it is used for carrying papers or files or books.

briefing.definition: giving detailed instructions, as for a military operation.

britt.definition: the young of a herring or sprat or similar fish.

broadcaster.definition: someone who broadcasts on radio or television.

broadcasting.definition: the medium that disseminates via telecommunications; radio and television.

broiled.definition: cooked by direct exposure to radiant heat.

brooding.definition: the process of sitting on eggs so as to hatch them by the warmth of the body; -- mostly used of birds.

browned.definition: having a tan color from exposure to the sun; -- of skin color.

bruised.definition: suffering from emotional injury; as, a bruised ego.

brunch.definition: a late breakfast or an early lunch.

bubbling.definition: giving off bubbles; -- of a liquid.

budgetary.definition: of or pertaining to a budget; as, budgetary considerations.

buffer.definition: to add a buffer{5} to (a solution), so as to reduce unwanted fluctuation of acidity.

buffered.definition: containing a buffer{5}; -- of solutions, usually aqueous solutions.

buffeted.definition: struck repeatedly; -- used especially of impact from winds, and sometimes metaphorically; as, buffeted by criticism.

bulging.definition: curving or bulging outward. Opposite of concave.

bullying.definition: Noisily domineering; tending to browbeat others.

bum.definition: To borrow without intention of returning; to cadge; as, to bum a cigarette; to bum a cup of coffee; -- usually with inexpensive items as the object.

bundled.definition: sold together as a single item; -- usually done for related products which work or are used together.

bunsen.definition: same as bunsen burner; a gas burner used in laboratories; has an air valve to regulate the mixture of gas and air.

burdened.definition: bearing a heavy load; as, a hiker burdened with a heavy backpack.

buried.definition: covered from view; as, her face buried (or hidden) in her hands; buried in the smoke of many rifles.

busted.definition: Inoperable due to damage; broken; -- of a machine; as, the coke machine is busted.

butadiene.definition: a gaseous hydrocarbon C4H6; -- it is used as a monomer unit in making synthetic rubbers.

butanol.definition: a flammable alcohol (C4H9.OH) derived from butane and used as a solvent.

butch.definition: a lesbian who is noticeably masculine.

buttocks.definition: the fleshy part of the human body at the back of the hip, on which a person sits.

buttoned.definition: furnished with buttons or something buttonlike. Opposite of unbuttoned.

buying.definition: the act of buying; as, buying equipment for the trip took several hours.

buyout.definition: the acquisition of ownership of a company by purchasing a controlling percentage of its stock.

dalton.definition: a unit of mass, approximately 1.66 x 10-24 grams; -- it is approximately equal to the mass of one hydrogen atom, but the exact value differs slightly as used in physics and chemistry. It is used mostly to describe the size of proteins and nucleic acids in biochemistry.

damaged.definition: changed so as to reduce value, function, or other desirable trait; -- usually not used of persons. Opposite of undamaged.

damages.definition: a sum of money paid in compensation for an injury or wrong.

damaging.definition: causing harm or injury; as, damaging to career and reputation.

darling.definition: Dearly beloved; regarded with especial kindness and tenderness; favorite.

darned.definition: an intensifying expletive; a euphemism for damned; as, for no darned reason at all.

database.definition: an organized body of related information.

dated.definition: marked by features of the immediate and usually discounted past.

daunting.definition: serving to discourage, dishearten, or intimidate; discouraging; disheartening. Opposite of encouraging.

dawning.definition: the first light of day; dawn.

daytime.definition: The time during which there is daylight, as distinguished from the night; same as day, 1; as, during the daytime.

dazed.definition: stupefied; conscious but unable to think clearly; -- usually caused by a blow or other shock.

deactivation.definition: The act or process of deactivating.

deadlock.definition: A lock which is not self-latching, but requires a key to throw the bolt forward.

deadly.definition: In a manner resembling, or as if produced by, death; deathly.

deafening.definition: extremely loud; so loud as to cause deafness; as, a disco with rock music played at a deafening volume.

decapitated.definition: having had the head cut off.

deceleration.definition: a decrease in velocity. Opposite of acceleration

decent.definition: Suitable in words, behavior, dress, or ceremony; becoming; fit; decorous; proper; seemly; as, decent conduct; decent language.

decentralization.definition: The action of decentralizing, or the state of being decentralized.

declared.definition: made known or openly avowed; as, their declared and their covert objectives; a declared liberal. Opposite of undeclared.

decode.definition: to convert from a coded form into the original form; -- of communications. Inverse of encode.

decolonization.definition: the action of changing from colonial to independent status.

decompression.definition: the process of experiencing decompression; the act or process of relieving or reducing pressure.

deconstruct.definition: To interpret (a text or an artwork) by the method of deconstruction.

deconstruction.definition: A philosophical theory of criticism (usually of literature or film) that seeks to expose deep-seated contradictions in a work by delving below its surface meaning. This method questions the ability of language to represent a fixed reality, and proposes that a text has no stable meaning because words only refer to other words, that metaphysical or ethnocentric assumptions about the meaning of words must be questioned, and words may be redefined in new contexts and new, equally valid and even contradictory meanings may be found. Such new interpretations may be based on the philosophical, political, or social implications of the words of a text, rather than solely on attempts to determine the author's intentions.

decontamination.definition: The removal of contaminants; as, the decontamination of a room after a spill of radioactive materials.

decor.definition: the layout, style, and furnishings of a livable interior.

decoration.definition: The act of adorning, embellishing, or honoring; ornamentation.

decreased.definition: made less in size or amount or degree. Opposite of increased.

dedicated.definition: wholly committed to a purpose or cause; as, a dedicated musician.

deeds.definition: performance of moral or religious acts; salvation is not by deeds, but by faith; to do good deeds.

dee.definition: an electrode with a large interior cavity, shaped like the letter "D", used in opposed pairs to accelerate particles in a cyclotron.

defenceless.definition: same as defenseless; as, a defenceless child.

deflation.definition: the act or process of deflating.

deflationary.definition: of or pertaining to deflation; as, deflationary signs.

deflator.definition: a statistical factor designed to remove the effect of inflation; inflation adjusted variables are in constant dollars; as, the GNP deflator..

deflect.definition: To cause to turn aside; to bend; as, rays of light are often deflected; to deflect a punch; to deflect criticism by acknowledging a mistake.

degenerate.definition: a person who has declined from a high standard, especially a sexual deviate; -- usually used disparagingly or opprobriously of persons whose sexual behavior does not conform to the norms of accepted morals.

degrading.definition: causing humiliation or degradation; as, a degrading surrender.

del.definition: a differential operator which, operating on a function of several variables, gives the sum of the partial derivatives of the function with respect to the three orthogonal spatial coordinates; -- also called the gradient or grad. It is represented by an inverted Greek capital delta (nabla, meaning harp in Hebrew.

delegating.definition: the act or process of authorizing subordinates to make certain decisions.

deluxe.definition: impressively expensive; notably exceeding typical price or quality.

demographic.definition: of or pertaining to demography; as, demographic surveys.

demography.definition: The study of vital statistics, such as births, deaths, marriages, mortality, health, etc., in populations and subgroups of populations.

demonstrated.definition: having been proved or verified beyond doubt; proved by demonstration.

demoralized.definition: made less hopeful or enthusiastic; rendered pessimistic; as, the demoralized Iraqi ground troops put up little resistance.

dental.definition: Of or pertaining to the teeth or to dentistry; as, dental surgery.

departed.definition: past; -- used of time; as, departed summers.

departing.definition: leaving a starting or stopping point on a journey; as, Departing flights were delayed by the snowstorm. Opposite of arriving.

dependability.definition: the trait of being dependable or reliable.

depicted.definition: represented graphically by sketch or design or lines.

depleted.definition: no longer sufficient; as, our funds are depleted.

deploy.definition: To place (people or other resources) into a position so as to be ready to for action or use.

deployment.definition: the arrangement or distribution (of resources such as people or equipment), in preparation for battle or work.

deprived.definition: marked by deprivation especially of the necessities of life or healthful environmental or social influences; as, a childhood that was unhappy and deprived, the family living off charity; boys from a deprived environment, wherein the family life revealed a pattern of neglect, moral degradation, and disregard for law.

deputy.definition: One appointed as the substitute of another, and empowered to act for him, in his name or his behalf; a substitute in office; a lieutenant; a representative; a delegate; a vicegerent; as, the deputy of a prince, of a sheriff, of a township, etc.

derogatory.definition: Tending to derogate, or lessen in value; expressing a low opinion; expressing derogation; detracting; injurious; -- with from, to, or unto.

descendants.definition: all of the offspring of a given progenitor.

desegregation.definition: the action of incorporating a racial or religious group into a community; the elimination of laws, regulations, or customs which prohibit members of a specific racial or national group from using certain locations, organizations, or facilities.

desensitization.definition: the process of reducing or eliminating sensitivity.

deserted.definition: having no residents; as, deserted villages.

deserve.definition: To be worthy of recompense; -- usually with ill or with well.

deserved.definition: properly earned; warranted; merited. Opposite of undeserved.

deservedly.definition: According to desert (whether good or evil); justly.

detailed.definition: Developed or executed with care and in minute detail; as, a detailed plan.

detente.definition: the easing of tensions or strained relations (especially between nations), as by agreement, negotiation, or tacit understandings.

deteriorate.definition: To grow worse; to be impaired in quality; to degenerate.

deterministic.definition: of or pertaining to determinism; as, deterministic theories.

detoxification.definition: a medically supervised treatment for addiction to drugs or alcohol intended to rid the body of the addictive substances.

devastating.definition: highly critical; making light of; as, a devastating portrait of human folly.

developed.definition: being changed over time so as to be e.g. stronger or more complete or more useful; as, the developed qualities of the Hellenic outlook; the state's well-developed industries. Opposite of undeveloped.

developing.definition: the process of treating a photosensitive material with chemicals in order to make a latent image visible.

deviate.definition: a person having behavior differing from that which is normal or socially acceptable; -- used especially to characterize persons whose sexual behavior is considered morally unacceptable.

deviation.definition: The act of deviating; a wandering from the way; variation from the common way, from an established rule, etc.; departure, as from the right course or the path of duty.

devil.definition: To make like a devil; to invest with the character of a devil.

dexamethasone.definition: a corticosteroid drug used to treat allergies or inflammation.

diabetes.definition: Any of several diseases which is attended with a persistent, excessive discharge of urine; when used without qualification, the term usually refers to diabetes mellitus. The most common form is diabetes mellitus, in which the urine is not only increased in quantity, but contains saccharine matter, and the condition if untreated is generally fatal.

diagnosing.definition: the act or process of identifying the nature or cause of some phenomenon.

dice.definition: To cut into small cubes; as, to slice and dice carrots.

dickie.definition: A small 3rd seat in the back of an old-fashioned 2-seat car.

differentiable.definition: possessing a differential coefficient or derivative; -- of a mathematical expression.

differentiated.definition: made different (especially in the course of development) or shown to be different; as, the differentiated markings of butterflies; the regionally differentiated results. Opposite of undifferentiated.

differential.definition: Relating to or indicating a difference; creating a difference; discriminating; special; as, differential characteristics; differential duties; a differential rate.

dig.definition: To understand; as, do you dig me?.

digit.definition: To point at or out with the finger.

digital.definition: Of or pertaining to the fingers; done with the fingers; as, digital compression; digital examination.

digoxin.definition: a steroid glycoside, one of the cardiotonic chemical substances which is extracted from the foxglove. It is a white, crystalline substance (C41H64O14), and is a 3-substituted triglucoside of a steroid, related structurally to digitalin and digitoxin. It is used as a cardiotonic for treatment of certain heart conditions, such as congestive heart failure. Chemically it is (34)-O-2,6-dideoxy-4)-2,6-dideoxy-. The related compounds digitalin and digoxin are also extracted from the foxglove (Digitalis lanata and Digitalis purpurea). The class of steroid glycosides having cardiotonic properties are referred to as the cardiac glycosides.

dinner.definition: The principal meal of the day, eaten in some countries about midday, but in others (especially in the U. S. and in large cities) at a later hour.

diploid.definition: having a number of chromosomes corresponding to two copies of each chromosome; having double the basic number of chromosomes, as seen in a haploid cell. Contrasted to haploid and polyploid.

dipped.definition: having an abnormal sagging of the spine, especially in horses.

directed.definition: having a specified direction; often used in combination; as, goal-directed.

directionality.definition: the property of a microphone or antenna of being more sensitive to signal arriving from one direction than from another.

dis.definition: to treat in a disrespectful manner; to insult, disparage or belittle.

disability.definition: State of being disabled; deprivation or want of ability; absence of competent physical, intellectual, or moral power, means, fitness, and the like.

disabled.definition: injured so as to be unable to function; as, disabled veterans.

disabling.definition: causing or having caused disability; rendering disabled; as, disabling injury.

disarming.definition: act of reducing or depriving of weapons.

discolored.definition: Altered in color; stained; spotted or streaked with foreign matter.

disconcerting.definition: hard to deal with; causing uncertainty or confusion about how to act or react.

disconnected.definition: marked by or composed of disconnected parts or sounds.

discredited.definition: being brought into disrepute; as, a discredited politician.

disenfranchised.definition: deprived of the rights of citizenship, especially the right to vote. Opposite of enfranchised.

disentangle.definition: To free from entanglement; to release from a condition of being intricately and confusedly involved or interlaced; to reduce to orderly arrangement; to straighten out; as, to disentangle a skein of yarn.

disfigured.definition: having the appearance spoiled; as, a disfigured face; strip mining left a disfigured landscape.

disgusted.definition: having a strong distaste from surfeit.

disheartened.definition: made less hopeful or enthusiastic; as, their lack of interest disheartened the instructor.

disheartening.definition: Causing loss of hope or enthusiasm.

disinfectant.definition: That which disinfects, especially an agent for killing or removing the microorganisms which cause infection. Commonly used disinfectants are chlorine, sodium hypochlorite solution, hydrogen peroxide, and alcohol.

disinfection.definition: The act of disinfecting; purification from infecting matter.

diskette.definition: a data-storage medium consisting of a small plastic disk coated with a thin layer of magnetizable material on one or both sides, enclosed in a stiff envelope with a radial slit. It is used in a specially designed disk drive, in which the disk is rotated at high speed, and which stores data on the disk by causing changes in the direction of magnetization of the magnetic layer as the disk spins and as sequential locations on the disk pass under the read-write head of the drive. Reading of the data occurs in the reverse process, by detection of the patterns of magnetization of the disk. Such disks are used to store data or programs for a microcomputer.

dislike.definition: A feeling of positive and usually permanent aversion to something unpleasant, uncongenial, or offensive; disapprobation; repugnance; displeasure; disfavor; -- the opposite of liking or fondness.

dislocated.definition: separated at the joint; -- used especially of limbs; as, a dislocated knee.

disoriented.definition: having lost one's bearings physically or mentally.

disparaging.definition: expressing a low opinion of; same as derogatory; as, disparaging remarks about the new house.

dispensed.definition: distributed or weighed out in carefully determined portions; as, medicines dispensed to the sick.

dispirited.definition: Depressed in spirits; deprived of cheer or enthusiasm; disheartened; discouraged; daunted.

dispossessed.definition: physically or spiritually homeless or deprived of security.

disqualified.definition: rendered ineligible by law or rule or provision; as, disqualified from voting.

disqualify.definition: To deprive of the qualities or properties necessary for any purpose; to render unfit; to incapacitate; -- with for or from before the purpose, state, or act.

disregard.definition: Not to regard; to pay no heed to; to omit to take notice of; to neglect to observe; to slight as unworthy of regard or notice; as, to disregard the admonitions of conscience.

disrupted.definition: Not continuous in time or space. Opposite of continuous.

dissatisfied.definition: in a state of sulky dissatisfaction.

disseminated.definition: Occurring in small portions scattered through some other substance; scattered widely.

disseminating.definition: serving to diffuse, disseminate, or disperse.

dissemination.definition: The act of disseminating, or the state of being disseminated; diffusion for propagation and permanence; a scattering or spreading abroad, as of ideas, beliefs, etc.

dissimulation.definition: The act of dissembling; a hiding under a false appearance; concealment by feigning; false pretension; hypocrisy.

dissipate.definition: To scatter completely; to disperse and cause to disappear; -- used esp. of the dispersion of things that can never again be collected or restored.

dissociate.definition: To separate from fellowship or union; to disunite; to disjoin; as, to dissociate the particles of a concrete substance.

dissolved.definition: changed from a solid to a liquid state by increase of temperature; melted. Opposite of unmelted.

distressed.definition: facing or experiencing financial trouble or difficulty; as, distressed companies need loans and technical advice.

distributed.definition: spread from a central location to multiple points or recipients. Opposite of concentrated.

distrust.definition: Doubt of sufficiency, reality, or sincerity; lack of confidence, faith, or reliance; as, distrust of one's power, authority, will, purposes, schemes, etc.

divorced.definition: having a marriage legally terminated and having not remarried.

docking.definition: a act of securing an arriving vessel with ropes or anchors.

dockyard.definition: A yard or storage place for all sorts of naval stores and timber for shipbuilding.

doctor.definition: A teacher; one skilled in a profession, or branch of knowledge; a learned man.

doctrinal.definition: Pertaining to, or containing, doctrine or something taught and to be believed; as, a doctrinal observation.

document.definition: That which is taught or authoritatively set forth; precept; instruction; dogma.

dodger.definition: One who dodges or evades; one who plays fast and loose, or uses tricky devices.

dogmatic.definition: One of an ancient sect of physicians who went by general principles; -- opposed to the Empiric.

doll.definition: a small, usually flexible figure representing a human being, especially a toy baby for a little girl; a child's puppet.

dollar.definition: A silver coin of the United States containing 371.25 grains of silver and 41.25 grains of alloy, that is, having a total weight of 412.5 grains.

dolomite.definition: A mineral consisting of the carbonate of lime and magnesia in varying proportions. It occurs in distinct crystals, and in extensive beds as a compact limestone, often crystalline granular, either white or clouded. It includes much of the common white marble. Also called bitter spar.

dolphin.definition: A cetacean of the genus Delphinus and allied genera (esp. Delphinus delphis); the true dolphin.

domesticated.definition: tame, tamed; -- of animals. Opposite of wild.

dominated.definition: controlled or ruled by superior authority or power.

dominating.definition: exercising influence or control. Opposite of subordinate.

donated.definition: given freely especially to a cause or fund; as, the donated van made their meal-on-wheels venture possible.

doorbell.definition: a bell or other sounding device, actuated by a push button at an outer door; the push button activating the bell; alos, the ringing of such a bell; as, I was in the shower and didn't hear the doorbell.

doorman.definition: someone who guards the entrance to a building.

dosimetry.definition: Measurement of doses; specif., a system of therapeutics which uses but few remedies, mostly alkaloids, and gives them in doses fixed by certain rules.

doubled.definition: rendered twice as great or twice as many.

doubles.definition: badminton played with two players on each side.

downcast.definition: Cast downward; directed to the ground, from bashfulness, modesty, dejection, or guilt.

downsizing.definition: the reduction of expenditures and personnel in order to become financial stable; -- of businesses.

downstairs.definition: Down the stairs; to a lower floor; as, she headed downstairs as soon as she heard the horn.

downwind.definition: on the side or in the direction away from the direction from which the wind is blowing; in the direction toward which the wind is blowing; as, good hunters stay downwind of their prey. Opposite of upwind, and windward.

drafting.definition: writing a first version to be filled out and polished later.

dragging.definition: painfully or tediously slow and boring; as, the dragging minutes.

dragon.definition: A fabulous animal, generally represented as a monstrous winged serpent or lizard, with a crested head and enormous claws, and regarded as very powerful and ferocious.

drained.definition: having lost much energy or emotion from vigorous activity; -- of people; as, the day's events left her completely drained of strength.

dramatization.definition: Act of dramatizing; a dramatic representation.

draped.definition: covered with or as if with clothes or a wrap or cloak; as, a beam draped with cobwebs. Contrasted with uncovered.

draw.definition: To cause to move continuously by force applied in advance of the thing moved; to pull along; to haul; to drag; to cause to follow.

drawer.definition: One who, or that which, draws

dreamlike.definition: resembling a dream; vague or fantastic; as, night invested the lake with a dreamlike quality.

dreamy.definition: Abounding in dreams or given to dreaming; appropriate to, or like, dreams; visionary.

dresser.definition: One who dresses; one who put in order or makes ready for use; one who on clothes or ornaments.

dropped.definition: born; -- used of an animal. Opposite of unborn.

droppings.definition: fecal matter of animals; plural of dropping{2}.

drugged.definition: under the influence of narcotics or hypnotic drugs.

druggist.definition: One who deals in drugs; especially, one who buys and sells drugs without compounding them; one who owns or operates a drugstore.

drugstore.definition: a retail shop where medicine and other articles are sold.

dumped.definition: p. p. of dump, v. t.; as, The money was there, dumped all over the floor.

dungeon.definition: A close, dark prison, commonly, under ground, as if the lower apartments of the donjon or keep of a castle, these being used as prisons.

dunno.definition: A slang shortening of I don't know or don't know; as, dunno where I lost my keys; Where'd he go? I dunno..

duplex.definition: something which is duplex; -- used mostly in reference to a living unit, such as an apartment, in a building having two similar living units.

duplication.definition: The act of duplicating, or the state of being duplicated; a doubling; a folding over; a fold.

duster.definition: One who, or that which, dusts; a utensil that frees from dust.

dusty.definition: Filled, covered, or sprinkled with dust; clouded with dust; as, a dusty table; a dusty attic; also, reducing to dust.

dwindling.definition: the act or process of becoming gradually less until little remains; as, there is no greater sadness that the dwindling away of a family.

dysfunctional.definition: impaired in function; especially of a bodily system or organ.

dyskinesia.definition: an abnormality in performing voluntary muscle movements.

dyslexia.definition: Any of various reading disorders caused by a damaged or congenitally faulty structure within the central nervous system, and causing an impairment of the ability to interpret spatial relationships or to integrate auditory and visual information. A common example is when letter sequences are interpreted as inverted in order, as in bat/tab.

hacker.definition: One who, or that which, hacks.

hajj.definition: A pilgrimage to Mecca; every Muslim must make this journey at least once.

hallowed.definition: belonging to or derived from or associated with a divine power; made holy. Opposite of unholy.

hallway.definition: an interior passage or corridor in a building, onto which rooms open.

handbag.definition: a small bag usually made of cloth, leather or a similar imitation material, and often having a strap to permit carrying it by slinging it over a shoulder, used by women to carry money and small personal items or accessories; as, she had to search under the cosmetics, hankies, and medicines in her handbag to find a comb.

handful.definition: As much as the hand will grasp or contain.

handicap.definition: An allowance of a certain amount of time or distance in starting, granted in a race to the competitor possessing inferior advantages; or an additional weight or other hindrance imposed upon the one possessing superior advantages, in order to equalize, as much as possible, the chances of success; as, the handicap was five seconds, or ten pounds, and the like.

handled.definition: fitted with or having having a handle; as, a handled magnifying glass is easier to use. Opposite of handleless.

handler.definition: one who trains or exhibits animals.

handover.definition: The act of relinquishing property or authority etc. to another; as, the handover of occupied territory to the original posssessors; the handover of power from the military back to the civilian authorities.

hands.definition: a person's power or discretionary action; as, my fate is in your hands.

handset.definition: The mouthpiece and earpiece of a communications device mounted on a single handle; as, when the telephone rings, pick up the handset.

hangar.definition: a large building at an airport where aircraft can be stored and maintained.

hangover.definition: An unpleasant feeling, such as a headache, occurring as an aftereffect from the use of drugs (especially alcohol).

haphazard.definition: Determined by chance, whimsy, or guesswork; unplanned; aimless; random; -- used mostly of human actions.

happening.definition: something that happens; an occurrence; an event.

harassed.definition: troubled persistently, especially with petty annoyances; as, harassed working mothers.

hardcover.definition: Same as hardback n. and a.

hardwood.definition: Made of the hard-to-cut wood of a broad-leaved tree, as e.g. oak; consisting of a hardwood; as, hardwood floors; -- of wood and wooden objects.

hardworking.definition: habitually working diligently and for long hours.

hassle.definition: to repeatedly annoy; as, He is known to hassle his staff when he is overworked.

heaps.definition: a large quantity. See heap, senses 2 and 3; as, he made heaps of money in the stock market.

heartbeat.definition: the audible and palpable rhythmic contraction and expansion of the arteries with each beat of the heart; as, he listened to her heartbeat with a stethoscope.

heated.definition: characterized by great warmth and intensity of feeling; as, a heated argument. Opposite of dispassionate, passionless.

heavyweight.definition: a wrestler who weighs more than 214 pounds.

hedged.definition: qualified; limited or restricted; as, a hedged promise.

heights.definition: a high place; the high part of a district; as, he doesn't like heights.

helping.definition: a quantity of food served as part of a meal.

hemolysis.definition: The lysis of erythrocytes with the release of hemoglobin; the breaking apart of red blood cells in the blood.

hemolytic.definition: of or pertaining to hemolysis; causing hemolysis.

hep.definition: A call used by drill instructors to count cadence during marching; used identically to hut and hup.

heralded.definition: widely publicized; as, the royal couple's much heralded world tour.

heroin.definition: a morphine derivative, diacetyl morphine, used to relieve severe pain and as a sedative. It is highly addictive, and its use is strictly controlled in the U.S. by federal law. It is a popular strong narcotic drug of abuse, in part because it is more soluble than morphine. It is sometimes included as one of the components of Brompton's mixture, used to control pain in terminallly ill patients.

hesitating.definition: holding back because of doubt or lack of confidence.

hierarchical.definition: Of or pertaining to a hierarchy; ordered in a hierarchy.

higher.definition: advanced in complexity or elaboration; as, higher mathematics.

highland.definition: of, located in, or characteristic of high or hilly country. Contrasted to lowland.

highlight.definition: The part of an image that has the most intense light.

hindsight.definition: understanding the nature of an event after it has happened; as, hindsight is always clearer than foresight.

hinterland.definition: a remote and undeveloped area; originally, the land or region lying behind the coast district. The term is used esp. with reference to the so-called doctrine of the hinterland, sometimes advanced, that occupation of the coast supports a claim to an exclusive right to occupy, from time to time, the territory lying inland of the coast.

hip.definition: Aware of the latest ideas, trends, fashions, and developments in popular music and entertainment culture; not square; -- same as hep.

hippie.definition: Someone who rejects the established culture, dresses casually, and advocates extreme liberalism in politics and lifestyle. Used especially of those in the late 1960's, mostly in their late teens and early twenties, who conspicuously rejected traditional culture by dressing casually, if male wore their hair long, and wore folksy or used clothing adorned with beads, headbands, and often flowers; they emphasized the importance of love and direct personal relations rather than success-oriented businesslike behavior, strove for spontaneity, sometimes lived communally, and in some cases tried to expand their consciousness by various psychological techniques such as meditation, or through the use of consciousness-altering drugs such as marijuana or LSD. By the end of the Vietnam war in the 1970's, the numbers of people living a visibly hippie lifestyle had dramatically decreased, though some people continue to develop similar views and live with the same outlook.

hired.definition: performing work for pay; as, hired hands.

historical.definition: Of or pertaining to history, or the record of past events; as, an historical poem; the historic page.

hitting.definition: The act of striking one thing against another; as, repeated hitting raised a large bruise

hogan.definition: An earth-covered Navajo lodge; it is traditionally built with the entrance facing east.

hollowed.definition: having a cavity within; as, canoe made of a hollowed log.

hologram.definition: A photographic image giving the observer a seemingly three-dimensional view of the represented object. The three-dimensional effect is produced by exposing a photographic recording medium to an interference pattern generated by a coherent beam of light (as from a laser) reflected from the subject, interacting with a beam directly from the source. The full three-dimensional effect requires illumination of the image with coherent light, but less perfect three-dimensional visual effects may also be observed when the hologram is illuminated with white light.

holography.definition: The process of producing holograms, usually requiring a source of coherent light, as from a laser.

hombre.definition: an informal term for a youth or man.

homeless.definition: Those people who have no permanent residence, especially those who live outdoors due to poverty; usually used in the definite phrase the homeless.

homelessness.definition: the state or condition of having no home, especially of living in the streets.

homeostasis.definition: The ability and tendency of certain systems to maintain a relatively constant internal state in spite of changes in external conditions; this ability is achieved by the presence of feedback mechanisms which can adjust the state of the system to compensate for changes in the state caused by the external environment. It is exemplified in homeothermal biological systems, such as animals which maintain relatively constant blood temperature and composition in spite of variations in external temperature or the composition of the food ingested.

homeostatic.definition: Of or pertaining to homeostasis; exhibiting homeostasis.

homework.definition: preparatory school work done outside school (especially at home).

homey.definition: having a feeling of home; cozy and comfortable; as, the homey everyday atmosphere; a restaurant with a homey atmosphere.

hominid.definition: Any animal of the family Hominidae, including modern man as well as extinct species of the genera Homo and Australopithecus.

homogenized.definition: formed by blending unlike elements, especially by reducing one element to particles and dispersing them throughout another substance.

homophobia.definition: A strong dislike or fear of homosexuals, especially to an unreasonable degree.

homophobic.definition: Disliking or fearing homosexuals to an unreasonable degree.

honour.definition: Same as honor; -- chiefly British usage.

honours.definition: A university degree with honors; -- a term used in Great Britain.

hoover.definition: to clean with a vacuum cleaner.

hospitalization.definition: medical care in a hospital; also, the period during which one receives care in a hospital.

hostilities.definition: a legal state created by a declaration of war and ended by official declaration, during which the international rules of war apply.

hr.definition: An abbreviation for hour, the period of time equal to 1/24th of a day.

humiliated.definition: brought low in condition or status; reduced in dignity; humbled; mortified.

hunched.definition: having the back and shoulders rounded; not erect; -- of people.

hushed.definition: having the sound level reduced; -- especially used of the noise of conversation; as, speaking in hushed tones.

hyperactivity.definition: An unusually high level of activity; -- used especially with respect to children who move around frequently and do not sit still very long, most noticeably in school. It is sometimes associated with attention deficit disorder.

hyperinflation.definition: an unusually rapid rate of monetary inflation, as when prices rise more than 100 per cent per year.

hypertension.definition: abnormally high blood pressure; especially, the chronic condition associated with persistent high blood pressure.

hypertensive.definition: A person who suffers from persistently high blood pressure.

hypertonic.definition: Having a higher osmotic pressure than a comparison solution; -- of an aqueous solution. Increasing the concentration of dissolved solids increases the osmotic pressure, and thus the tonicity of a solution. Opposite of hypotonic and contrasting with isotonic.

hyperthyroidism.definition: An abnormality of the thyroid gland characterized by the pathologically excessive production of thyroid hormones; -- also, the resulting condition characterized by increased metabolism, weight loss, rapid heart rate, high blood pressure, an enlarged thyroid gland and sometimes exophthalmos. It leads to, and may be confirmed by, high plasma levels of triiodothyronine or thyroxin.

hyperventilation.definition: The act or process of hyperventilating; breathing rapidly and deeply.

lab.definition: Of or pertaining to a laboratory; as, a lab bench.

labourer.definition: a laborer; someone who works with their hands.

lactating.definition: actively producing milk; -- of female mammals.

lactose.definition: The main sugar present in milk, called also sugar of milk or milk sugar. When isolated pure it is obtained crystalline; it is separable from the whey by evaporation and crystallization. It is a disaccharide with the formula C12H22O11, being chemically 4-(. It has a slightly sweet taste, is dextrorotary, and is much less soluble in water than either cane sugar or glucose. Formerly called lactin. When hydrolyzed it yields glucose and galactose. In cells it may be hydrolyzed by the enzyme 1913 Webster +PJC]

lagoon.definition: A shallow sound, channel, pond, or lake, especially one into which the sea flows; as, the lagoons of Venice.

laminated.definition: Consisting of, or covered with, laminae, or thin plates, sheets, scales, or layers, one over another; laminate.

lancers.definition: A set of quadrilles for 8 or 16 couples.

landholding.definition: ownership of land; the state or fact of owning land.

landlady.definition: A woman having real estate which she leases to a tenant or tenants.

largest.definition: greatest in size of those under consideration.

larval.definition: Of or pertaining to a larva.

larynx.definition: The expanded upper end of the windpipe or trachea, connected with the hyoid bone or cartilage. It contains the vocal cords, which produce the voice by their vibrations, when they are stretched and a current of air passes between them. The larynx is connected with the pharynx by an opening, the glottis, which, in mammals, is protected by a lidlike epiglottis.

laser.definition: A device which produces an intense, usually narrow, monochromatic beam of coherent light; called also optical maser. It has various forms, and is used in various applications in science and technology. The beam is produced by boosting the majority of the electrons in specific radiation-absorbing atoms in a medium into a higher energy level, from which they are stimulated by their own emitted radiation to drop back synchronously to their lower energy level, and emit light which is in phase (coherent).

latched.definition: secured by means of a latch against opening.

lateral.definition: To pass the footbal to a receiver who is behind the passer; to make a lateral pass; as, the ball was lateraled to the fullback, who ran it for a touchdown.

launcher.definition: a device capable of launching a rocket.

launching.definition: the act of moving a newly-built vessel into the water for the first time.

laurels.definition: An honor or honors conferred for some notable achievement.

leaders.definition: the body of people who lead a group; the leadership{3}; as, they hung the leaders of the insurrection.

leaking.definition: having liquid seeping in or out through openings; leaky.

leather.definition: Of, pertaining to or made of leather; consisting of leather; as, a black leather jacket.

leftist.definition: a person who belongs to the political left.

leftover.definition: An unused part or portion; -- used especially of food remaining uneaten from a previous meal; as, to have leftovers for dinner.

lefty.definition: a person who uses the left hand with greater skill than the right; a left-handed person.

legislating.definition: the act of making or enacting laws; legislation{1}.

lessening.definition: a change downward; a decrease; a reduction.

leukaemia.definition: A disease in which the white corpuscles of the blood are largely increased in number, and there is enlargement of the spleen, or the lymphatic glands; formerly called leucocythaemia. It is due to a cancer of the bone marrow, and results in anemia and increased susceptibility to infectious disease.

levodopa.definition: A substance used as a therapy for Parkinson's Disease; the L form of Dopa; L-dihydroxyphenylalanine; L-hydroxytyrosine (C9H11NO4); also called L-dopa. In the body it is converted by the enzyme dopa-decarboxylase into dopamine, the form in which it is active in the brain, affecting neural impulse transmission.

lexical.definition: Of or pertaining to a lexicon, to lexicography, or words; according or conforming to a lexicon.

liaison.definition: A union, or bond of union; an intimacy; an interrelationship.

liberated.definition: released from chemical combination, or as a consequence of chemical reaction; -- of a gas.

liberating.definition: giving freedom from restriction or restraint.

libidinal.definition: Of or pertaining to the libido; caused by libido; as, libidinal gratification; libidinal impulses.

libido.definition: Sexual desire; the sexual instinct; the sex drive.

lifeline.definition: The anem given to one of the creases on the palm; its length is said by palmists to indicate how long one will live.

lifted.definition: turned upward; as, she left the room with her face lifted.

lightening.definition: The process of changing to a lighter color.

lights.definition: The lungs of an animal or bird; -- sometimes coarsely applied to the lungs of a human being.

limbic.definition: of or pertaining to the limbic system; as, the limbic system.

lime.definition: having a yellowish-green color like that of the lime (the fruit).

limelight.definition: That part of the stage upon which the limelight is cast, usually where the most important action is progressing or where the leading player or players are placed and upon which the attention of the spectators is therefore concentrated.

liminal.definition: of or pertaining to a limen, especially a sensory threshhold.

lindy.definition: an energetic American dance that was popular in the 1930s (probably named for the aviator Charles Lindbergh).

lined.definition: furnished with items in a line or as if in a line.

lipid.definition: Any of a variety of oily or greasy organic compounds found as major structural components of living cells; they are insoluble in water but soluble in organic solvents such as alcohol and ether, and include the common fats, cholesterol and other steroids, phospholipids, sphingolipids, waxes, and fatty acids; some of the lipids, together with proteins and carbohydrates, form an essential structural component of living cells, as in the cell walls and membranes. The term lipid refers to its solubility in nonpolar solvents, and has no significance with regard to chemical structure.

lipophilic.definition: having an affinity for lipids; -- of chemical substances or parts of molecules. Contrasted to lipophobic or polar.

liquefied.definition: converted to a liquid; as, liquified natural gas; liquified coal.

listed.definition: placed on a list. Opposite of unlisted.

littered.definition: having articles scattered about in a disorderly fashion.

loaded.definition: containing as much or as many as is possible; -- of containers, vehicles, trays, etc.; as, a tray loaded with dishes

loads.definition: A large quantity; a lot; as, loads of fun.

localized.definition: confined or restricted to a particular location; as, the localized infection formed a definite abscess. Contrasted with disseminated or systemic.

located.definition: situated in a particular spot or position; as, valuable centrally located urban land.

locating.definition: the act of putting something in a certain place or location.

loma.definition: A lobe; a membranous fringe or flap.

lookup.definition: an operation that determines whether one or more of a set of items has a specified property; as, they wrote a program to do a table lookup.

looted.definition: wrongfully emptied or stripped of anything of value; as, the robbers left the looted train.

losses.definition: something lost, especially money lost at gambling. Inverse of winnings.

loudspeaker.definition: A device which converts electrical signals into sounds loud enough to be heard at a distance, usually outdoors; it is used to amplify or transmit over a distance speech from a person, who is typically speaking into a microphone. Sometimes it is used to play recorded speech or music.

loved.definition: p. p. of love, v. t.. Opposite of unloved.

lowered.definition: pointed downward; as, with lowered eyes. Opposite of raised.

lubricated.definition: smeared with oil or grease to reduce friction.

lullaby.definition: A song to quiet babes or lull them to sleep; that which quiets.

lunchtime.definition: the time for eating lunch; as, he observed a regular lunchtime.

lx.definition: the Roman numeral representation of sixty; six times ten; -- a determinate quantifier.

lxx.definition: the Roman numeral representation of seventy; seven times ten; -- a determinate quantifier.

tackle.definition: An act of tackling{4}; as, brought down by a tackle by a lineman.

takeover.definition: The acquisition of ownership of one company by another company, usually by purchasing a controlling percentage of its stock or by exchanging stock of the purchasing company for that of the purchased company. It is a hostile takeover if the management of the company being taken over is opposed to the deal. A hostile takeover is sometimes organized by a corporate raider.

talk.definition: To utter words; esp., to converse familiarly; to speak, as in familiar discourse, when two or more persons interchange thoughts.

thank.definition: A expression of gratitude; an acknowledgment expressive of a sense of favor or kindness received; obligation, claim, or desert, or gratitude; -- now generally used in the plural.

thaw.definition: The melting of ice, snow, or other congealed matter; the resolution of ice, or the like, into the state of a fluid; liquefaction by heat of anything congealed by frost; also, a warmth of weather sufficient to melt that which is congealed.

thou.definition: The second personal pronoun, in the singular number, denoting the person addressed; thyself; the pronoun which is used in addressing persons in the solemn or poetical style.

threads.definition: Clothes; clothing; as, he was wearing his new threads at the party.

thymus.definition: Of, pertaining to, or designating, the thymus gland.

titanic.definition: Of or pertaining to titanium; derived from, or containing, titanium; specifically, designating those compounds of titanium in which it has a higher valence as contrasted with the titanous compounds.

torture.definition: To put to torture; to pain extremely; to harass; to vex.

tough.definition: A person who is tough{7}; a ruffian; a thug; as, a cluster of neighborhood toughs hanging out on the corner.

tritium.definition: A radioactive isotope of hydrogen having one proton and two neutrons in the nucleus. It decays spontaneously to Helium-3 by the emission of an electron (beta ray), with a half-life of 12.3 years. Symbol 1H3. Atomic weight 3.01605 (C-12 = 12.0000). It is one of the radioisotopes commonly used to label chemical compounds for use as tracers in biochemistry and chemistry. It is also used as one of the fusionable components of a hydrogen bomb.

turbo.definition: Any one of numerous marine gastropods of the genus Turbo or family Turbinidae, usually having a turbinate shell, pearly on the inside, and a calcareous operculum.

turnkey.definition: Of or pertaining to a building, complex device, system, or industrial installation which is sold by a contractor only after it is ready for immediate occupation or use; fully functional and ready for use; -- used of complex systems of a type which often require preparation or installation by the user before being capable of functioning as intended; as, a turnkey ethylene production plant; a turnkey apartment building.

tutorial.definition: A class{6} or short series of classes in which one or more instructors provide intensive instruction on some subject to a small group. Such short courses of instruction may be held at an institution of learning, or in any other place where a small group may desire a brief but thorough introduction to a topic.

yahoo.definition: One of a race of filthy brutes resembling men but subject to the Houyhnhnms in Swift's Webster 1913 Suppl. + WordNet 1.5 + CM]

yang.definition: One of the two fundamental principles. See yin and yang.

yearning.definition: full of longing or unfulfilled desire.

yelling.definition: The uttering of one or more loud inarticulate cries, as of pain or excitement.

mac.definition: Shortened form of mackintosh, a waterproof raincoat made of rubberized fabric.

macabre.definition: portraying human injury or death in a way so as to inspiring shock or horror; gruesome; ghastly; as, macabre tortures conceived by madmen.

machismo.definition: A strong, and by some considered exaggerated, sense of manly pride, associated with an attitude that the proper expression of masculinity includes virility, courage, and an entitlement to dominate, especially over women.

macho.definition: Manly, especially with an assertive and domineering manner toward women.

macro.definition: very large in scale or scope or capability; as, macroeconomics.

macromolecular.definition: Of, pertaining to, or consisting of macromolecules.

maddened.definition: filled with or indicating extreme anger.
