madras.definition: A large silk-and-cotton kerchief, usually of bright colors, such as those often used by negroes for turbans.

mag.definition: Shortened form of magazine, the periodic paperback publication.

magenta.definition: An aniline dye obtained as an amorphous substance having a green bronze surface color, which dissolves to a shade of red; also, the color; -- so called from Magenta, in Italy, in allusion to the battle fought there about the time the dye was discovered. Called also fuchsin, fuchsine, roseine, etc.

magneto.definition: A small electric generator with an armature rotating in a magnetic field, having a secondary winding that generates a high voltage, such as one used to generate a voltage sufficient to cause a spark to jump between the poles of a spark plug in an internal-combustion engine.

magnetosphere.definition: the magnetic field of a planet; the volume around the planet in which charged particles are subject more to the planet's magnetic field than to the solar magnetic field.

magnum.definition: Having a larger charge than usual for a cartridge of the same caliber; -- of cartridges for handgun; as, a .44 magnum cartridge.

magus.definition: a magician or sorcerer of ancient times.

mailbox.definition: A public box for deposit of mail, where it is later picked up by the postal authority for delivery.

mailing.definition: The act or process of sending materials through the mail.

main.definition: A hand or match at dice.

mainframe.definition: A large digital computer serving 100-400 users and occupying a special air-conditioned room. At any given point in development of computer technology, the mainframe will be faster, have large main memeory, and be more capable than a minicomputer, which will in turn be faster and more capable than a personal computer. The typical personal computer in 1999 is faster than a mainframe was in 1970.

mainline.definition: to inject (illegal drugs) into the vein; as, he preferred to mainline heroin rather than sniff coke.

mains.definition: The source of electrical power in a building; the wiring system of a building.

mainstream.definition: TO place (a student) in regular school classes; -- used especially of mentally or physically handicapped children.

maize.definition: A large species of American grass of the genus Zea (Zea Mays), widely cultivated as a forage and food plant; Indian corn, commonly called corn. Also, its seed, growing on cobs, and used as food for men and animals.

majors.definition: The teams in the major leagues.

make.definition: To cause to exist; to bring into being; to form; to produce; to frame; to fashion; to create.

makeshift.definition: That with which one makes shift; a temporary expedient, with implication of inferiority to the more usual object or means.

malady.definition: Any disease of the human body; a distemper, disorder, or indisposition, proceeding from impaired, defective, or morbid organic functions; especially, a lingering or deep-seated disorder.

malaria.definition: Air infected with some noxious substance capable of engendering disease; esp., an unhealthy exhalation from certain soils, as marshy or wet lands, producing fevers; miasma.

malice.definition: Enmity of heart; malevolence; ill will; a spirit delighting in harm or misfortune to another; a disposition to injure another; a malignant design of evil.

malign.definition: Having an evil disposition toward others; harboring violent enmity; malevolent; malicious; spiteful; -- opposed to benign.

malignant.definition: Disposed to do harm, inflict suffering, or cause distress; actuated by extreme malevolence or enmity; virulently inimical; bent on evil; malicious.

malnourished.definition: Not getting adequate food; suffering from malnutrition; underfed.

malnutrition.definition: Faulty or imperfect nutrition; inadequate or unbalanced food intake.

maltreatment.definition: Cruel or inhumane treatment; ill usage; abuse.

mammy.definition: A child's name for mamma, mother.

manger.definition: A trough or open box in which fodder is placed for horses or cattle to eat.

manipulative.definition: Any object given to children to encourage them to learn by manipulating physical objects; applied especially to solid objects of varying geometrical shape that can be fit together to form larger aggregates.

mankind.definition: The human race; man, taken collectively.

manned.definition: Having a crew; -- of vehicles; as, a manned earth satellite was considered a necessary research step; to minimize casualties, the military used cruise missiles rather than manned aircraft for the bombardment. Opposite of unmanned.

mannitol.definition: A white crystalline hexose (HO.CH2.(CHOH)4.CH2.OH) of a sweet taste obtained from a so-called manna, the dried sap of the flowering ash (Fraxinus ornus); -- called also mannite, and hydroxy hexane. Cf. Dulcite. It is used in pharmacy as excipient and diluent for solids and liquids. It is also used as a food additive for anti-caking properties, or as a sweetener, and, illegally, to "cut" (dilute) illegal drugs such as cocaine or heroin.

manually.definition: By hand. In some contexts, contrasted with automatically.

manufactured.definition: Produced in a large-scale industrial operation. Contrasted with hand-made.

manure.definition: Any matter which makes land productive; a fertilizing substance.

mapping.definition: A function such that for every element of one set there is a unique element of another set. Same as map{4}.

marbles.definition: A children's game played with marbles{3}, little balls made of a hard substance (as glass).

marginality.definition: the property of being marginal or on the fringes.

maria.definition: Plural form of mare, a dark region of considerable extent on the surface of the moon.

marijuana.definition: A strong-smelling Asian plant (Cannabis sativa), also called hemp, from which a number of euphorogenic and hallucinogenic drugs are prepared. The euphoric effect is predominantly due to tetrahydrocannabinol (THC).

marketplace.definition: an area in a town where a public market is set up; a market place; a market{2}.

markup.definition: The amount added to the cost to determine the asking price.

martel.definition: To make a blow with, or as with, a hammer.

marten.definition: Any one of several fur-bearing carnivores of the genus Martes (formerly Mustela), closely allied to the sable. Among the more important species are the European beech marten or stone marten (Martes foina); the pine marten (Martes martes); and the American marten, or sable (Martes Americana), which some Zoologists consider only a variety of the Russian sable.

mascara.definition: A cosmetic used to darken and thicken the eye lashes, usually applied with a small brush.

masculine.definition: Of the male sex; not female.

masjid.definition: A Muslim place of worship; a mosque.

massif.definition: A block of the earth's crust bounded by faults and shifted to form peaks of a mountain range.

massive.definition: Forming, or consisting of, a large mass; compacted; weighty; heavy; massy.

masturbation.definition: The act of masturbating; sexual self-gratification; onanism.

matching.definition: having identical or closely similar appearance or properties; as, a pair of matching candlesticks.

mated.definition: Brought together for sexual activity; bred; -- of animals.

maternity.definition: Of or pertaining to childbirth or the period during which a woman is pregnant; as, maternity care; a maternity hospital.

matinee.definition: A reception, or a musical or dramatic entertainment, held in the daytime. See Soir.

matriarchal.definition: Of or pertaining to a matriarch; governed by a matriarch or matriarchs; as, a matriarchal society.

matrilineal.definition: tracing descent through the female line.

matte.definition: Having a dull, lusterless surface finish; opposed to glossy or polished; as, a matte photograph; a proof coin with matte figures on a polished field.

maximizing.definition: Making as great as possible; increasing to the highest degree.

maxwell.definition: A CGS unit of magnetic flux, abbreviated Mx; it is equal to the magnetic flux passing through one square centimeter which is normal to a magnetic field of one gauss.

mayhem.definition: The maiming of a person by depriving him of the use of any of his members which are necessary for defense or protection. See Maim.

mayonnaise.definition: A thick white sauce compounded of raw yolks of eggs beaten up with olive oil to the consistency near to that of a gel, and seasoned with vinegar, pepper, salt, etc.; -- used in dressing salads, fish, etc. Also, a dish dressed with this sauce.

mayor.definition: The chief magistrate of a city or borough; the chief administrative officer of a municipal corporation. In some American cities there is a city court of which the major is chief judge. The post is usually elective, its holder chosen by the electorate of the entire city.

mayoral.definition: Of or pertaining to a mayor; as, the mayoral limousine.

meaningful.definition: Having a meaning or purpose; having significance; as, a meaningful explanation; a meaningful discussion; a meaningful pause; to live a meaningful life. Opposite of meaningless.

meaningfulness.definition: the quality of having great meaning or value.

meaningless.definition: having no meaning; of no value; as, a meaningless endeavor; a meaningless life; a meaningless explanation. Opposite of meaningful.

measure.definition: A standard of dimension; a fixed unit of quantity or extent; an extent or quantity in the fractions or multiples of which anything is estimated and stated; hence, a rule by which anything is adjusted or judged.

mechanization.definition: The act or process of mechanizing.

media.definition: The latinic plural form of medium, sometimes used as a singular noun with the same meaning as medium; as, (Computers) place your installation media into the device which will read it; (Microbiology) the tuberculosis bacterium will only grow in a special media.

medicaid.definition: A program controlled by the United States government to provide health care for the needy. It is funded by contributions from the salaries of workers, and is therefore a form of health insurance.

mediocre.definition: Of a middle quality; of but a moderate or low degree of excellence; indifferent; ordinary.

megalithic.definition: Of or pertaining to megaliths or the period during which they were erected; as, megalithic monuments like Stonehenge.

meiotic.definition: Of or pertaining to meiosis; as, meiotic division.

melatonin.definition: A hormone secreted by the pineal gland. Chemically it is N-acety-5-methoxytryptamine. Research has indicated that there are daily rhythms in secretion of melatonin, in particular due to the depressing effect on melatonin production by light received by the retina. Conversely it appears that melatonin may influence the circadian rhythms of animals. There is some experimental evidence that administration of melatonin may increase the amount of sleep in people with sleep disorders. However, the evidence is not convincing and the effect is not profound. Nevertheless, the deregulation of melatonin and its availability over-the-counter has led to many people taking melatonin to help sleep, without consulting a physician.

mem.definition: the 13th letter of the Hebrew alphabet.

memorabilia.definition: Things remarkable and worthy of remembrance or record; also, the record of them.

meningeal.definition: Of or pertaining to the meninges.

menu.definition: The details of a banquet; a list of the dishes served at a meal, whether or not one has a choice.

merchandising.definition: The activities associated with selling products, such as identification of the market{7}, advertising at the right time in the right media{7}, and creating attractive packaging and displays; also, the study of the best methods to accomplish such goals.

merge.definition: To cause to be swallowed up; to immerse; to sink; to absorb.

merged.definition: formed or united into a whole; -- of formerly separate objects, groups, etc.

merging.definition: The act or process of joining together into one entity.

mesa.definition: A high tableland; a plateau on a hill.

metaphor.definition: The transference of the relation between one set of objects to another set for the purpose of brief explanation; a compressed simile; e. g., the ship plows the sea.

methadone.definition: a narcotic drug similar to morphine but less habit-forming; used in treating heroin addiction.

methanol.definition: The simplest alcohol of the paraffin series, CH3.OH; methyl alcohol. Called also wood alcohol. It is used as an antifreeze solvent, as a fuel, and as a denaturant for ethyl alcohol.

microcomputer.definition: A small computer based on a microprocessor; in practise, at any given time in the technology of computer development, a microcomputer will be one that is less powerful than a minicomputer.

micron.definition: A measure of length; the thousandth part of one millimeter; the millionth part of a meter.

microphone.definition: An instrument for converting sounds into electrical signals, for the purpose of recording or amplifying the sounds. It produces its effects in various ways, as for example by the changes of intensity in an electric current, occasioned by the variations in the contact resistance of conducting bodies, especially of imperfect conductors, under the action of acoustic vibrations. Other forms of microphone may use changes in capacitance or other phenomena to transduce the sounds into electrical signals.

midair.definition: some point in the air; above ground level; as, the planes collided in midair; also used attributively; as, a midair collision.

midterm.definition: the middle of the gestation period.

midwestern.definition: Of or pertaining to the Midwest region of the U. S., generally including Ohio; Indiana; Illinois; Iowa; Missouri; Kansas; Nebraska; and sometimes Michigan; Wisconsin; Minnesota; as, a midwestern city; midwestern accent.

migraine.definition: A kind of intense sick or nervous headache, usually periodical and confined to one side of the head; called also migraine headache. Same as megrim.

mike.definition: A microphone, the device for converting sound waves into electrical energy.

mil.definition: One million dollars; as, his new house cost over a mil.

militaristic.definition: imbued with militarism, in senses 3 or 4.

militarization.definition: act of assembling and putting into readiness the military forces for war or other emergency.

millet.definition: The name of several cereal and forage grasses which bear an abundance of small roundish grains. The common millets of Germany and Southern Europe are Panicum miliaceum, and Setaria Italica.

mimeo.definition: to make copies of using a mimeograph.

mina.definition: An ancient weight or denomination of money, of varying value. The Attic mina was valued at a hundred drachmas.

mined.definition: extracted from a source of supply as of minerals from the earth.

mineralized.definition: containing or impregnated with minerals; as, mineralized water; red stains that signify mineralized land.

minicomputer.definition: a mid-sized digital computer; at any given point in the development of computer technology, a minicomputer will be faster and have greater capacity than a microcomputer, but will be slower and have less capacity than a mainframe computer.

minimize.definition: To reduce to the smallest part or proportion possible; to reduce to a minimum.

minimized.definition: Reduced to the smallest possible size or amount or degree.

minors.definition: The minor leagues, those leagues of professional sports teams less proficient than the majors, or major leagues.

mint.definition: Like new; in brand-new condition; unworn, as a coin recently made at a mint{1}; as, he had a '53 Cadillac in mint condition.

minus.definition: A factor counted as a disadvantage; a loss or potential loss in a situation or plan; as, he added up all the pluses and minuses and decided not to do it; as, the lack of money is a big minus in an election campaign.

minuscule.definition: Of or relating to a minuscule{2} or of a script written in minuscules{2}; of the size and style of minuscules{2}; written in minuscules{2}; minuscular.

mirrored.definition: Reflected in or as if in a mirror.

misalignment.definition: The act of aligning improperly or state of being improperly aligned.

mismatched.definition: Matched unsuitably; grouped into pairs or sets with incompatible characteristics.

mist.definition: Visible watery vapor suspended in the atmosphere, at or near the surface of the earth; fog.

mitigating.definition: serving to reduce blame; -- of situations; as, mitigating factors; mitigating circumstances. Opposite of aggravating.

mnemonic.definition: Something used to assist the memory, as an easily remembered acronym or verse.

modeled.definition: resembling sculpture; as, her finely modeled features.

modem.definition: An electronic device that converts electronic signals into sound waves, and sound waves into electronic signals, used to transmit information between computers by the use of ordinary telephone lines; also called modulator-demodulator; as, the latest modems can transmit data at 56,000 baud over a clear telephone line. The speed of transmission of information by a modem is usually measured in units of baud, equivalent to bits per second.

moderated.definition: having elements or qualities mixed in proper or suitable proportions; especially, made less severe. Contrasted with harsh.

moderating.definition: lessening in intensity or strength. Opposite of intensifying.

modulated.definition: Having either amplitude, intensity, frequency, or phase altered at intervals to represent information to be transmitted; -- of the carrier wave of a radio signal transmitted from one device to another for the purpose of conveying information. Opposite of unmodulated.

mol.definition: A quantity of a substance equal to the molecular weight of a substance expressed in grams; a gram molecule; the basic unit of amount of substance adopted under the System International d'Unites; as, he added two mols of dextrose to the medium.

molar.definition: Being at a concentration having the designated number of moles (of solute) per liter of solvent; as, an 0.2 molar solution of sodium chloride in water is close to isotonic.

mole.definition: A quantity of a substance equal to the molecular weight of a substance expressed in grams; a gram molecule; the basic unit of amount of substance adopted under the System International d'Unites; as, he added two moles of sodium chloride to the medium.

monetarist.definition: One who adheres to the theory of monetarism.

monogram.definition: To inscribe or ornament with a monogram.

monolingual.definition: Using or knowing only one language; as, monolingual speakers; a monolingual dictionary. Opposite of multilingual.

monomer.definition: The basic conceptual building unit of a polymer; a molecule of low molecular weight which may combine with other molecules to form a molecule in a chain or branched form having high molecular weight; as, amino acids are the monomer units which are combined to form proteins; vinylic plastics are formed from monomers having a vinyl group.

monomeric.definition: Not linked to other molecules of the same kind; having the property of a monomer. Opposed to polymeric.

monsoon.definition: A wind blowing part of the year from one direction, alternating with a wind from the opposite direction; -- a term applied particularly to periodical winds of the Indian Ocean, which blow from the southwest from the latter part of May to the middle of September, and from the northeast from about the middle of October to the middle of December.

moose.definition: A large cervine mammal (Alces alces syn. Alces machlis, syn Alces Americanus), native of the Northern United States and Canada. The adult male is about as large as a horse, and has very large, palmate antlers. It closely resembles the European elk, and by many Zoologists is considered the same species. See Elk.

moot.definition: A ring for gauging wooden pins.

moralistic.definition: narrowly and conventionally moral; -- of people.

morals.definition: motivation based on ideas of right and wrong.

morel.definition: Nightshade; -- so called from its blackish purple berries.

morph.definition: To transform smoothly in imperceptible steps from one image to another, on a computer screen.

morpheme.definition: The smallest unit of meaning of a language, which cannot be divided into smaller parts carrying meaning; it is usually smaller than a single wordform, such as the -ed morpheme of verbs in the past tense or the -s morpheme of nouns in the plural form.

morphogenesis.definition: The development of the tissues and organs of an organism; the formation of structural features of an organism.

morphogenetic.definition: Of or pertaining to morphogenesis; concerned with the process of development of the normal features of an organism.

mortgaged.definition: burdened with legal or financial obligations; as, His house was mortgaged to the hilt.

motherboard.definition: The board containing the main circuits of an electronic device, especially computers. The term is used primarily in microcomputer literature, where it designates the board containing the main expansion bus, and usually also the cpu. On motherboards designed with an expansion bus, often all of the circuits not contained on an expansion card are on the motherboard.

motivated.definition: Having a strong motive; -- of people. Opposite of unmotivated.

motivation.definition: The act or process of motivating.

motorized.definition: same as motored; as, a motorized wheelchair. Opposite of unmotorized.

mountaineer.definition: To live or act as a mountaineer; to climb mountains.

mu.definition: The 12th letter of the Greek alphabet (WordNet 1.5]

muck.definition: To excavate and remove muck{5}. Often used with out, as, to muck out a round.

mucosa.definition: The mucus-secreting membrane lining all body cavities or passages that communicate with the exterior; called also mucous membrane.

muffled.definition: same as muted; as, muffled drums; the muffled noises of the street.

mufti.definition: Ordinary civilian dress when worn by persons who serve in a uniformed service, such as the military or police. It originally was used in reference to British naval or military officers, and originated with the British service in India.

mug.definition: To take property from (a person) in a public place by threatening or committing violence on the person who is robbed; to rob, especially to rob by use of a weapon such as a knife or gun.

murdered.definition: killed unlawfully; as, the murdered woman.

muscle.definition: To compel by threat of force; as, they muscled the shopkeeper into paying protection money.

mutagenesis.definition: the causing of a mutation or the occurrence of a mutation{3}.

mutation.definition: Change; alteration, either in form or qualities.

muted.definition: same as quiet; as, the muted atmosphere of a church. Opposite of noisy.

mutilated.definition: badly injured, perhaps with amputation or permanent disfigurement; as, mutilated victims of the rocket attack.

mutt.definition: An dog that is of inferior quality or of mixed breed.

mycobacteria.definition: A group of rod-shaped bacteria, some saprophytic or causing diseases.

mycobacterium.definition: Any of various rod-shaped bacteria, some saprophytic or causing diseases.

myocardial.definition: Of or pertaining to the myocardium.

mystique.definition: An aura of reverence or mystery stemming from feelings of high value or interest or meaning surrounding a person or thing; as, the Kennedy mystique.

jaded.definition: dulled by surfeit; as, the amoral, jaded, bored upper classes.

jagged.definition: Having jags; having rough, sharp notches, protuberances, or teeth; cleft; laciniate; divided; as, jagged rocks.

jailed.definition: placed in a prison; -- of people.

jammed.definition: filled to capacity or overfilled; as, the auditorium was jammed to the rafters.

jazz.definition: A type of music that originated in New Orleans around 1900 and developed through increasingly complex styles, but generally featuring intricate rhythms, improvisation, prominent solo segments, and great freedom in harmonic idiom played frequently in a polyphonic style, on various instruments including horn, saxophone, piano and percussion, but rarely stringed instruments.

jeopardize.definition: To expose to loss or injury; to risk.

jerky.definition: Meat, especially beef, that has been cut in strips and dried; meat that has been jerked; see first jerk, v.; as, beef jerky

jewelled.definition: covered with beads or jewels or sequins.

jimmy.definition: To pry open (a door, window, etc.) with a jimmy or similar device; often used with open; as, the burglar jimmied open the back door and stole the TV set.

jock.definition: a person trained to compete in sports; an athlete.

joey.definition: Any young animal, especially a young kangaroo.

joking.definition: intended as a joke; -- of communications.

joule.definition: A unit of work which is equal to 107 ergs (the unit of work in the C. G. S. system of units), and is equivalent to one watt-second, the energy expended in one second by an electric current of one ampere in a resistance of one ohm; also called the absolute joule. It is abbreviated J or j. The international joule is slightly larger, being 1.000167 times the absolute joule. The absolute joule is approximately equal to 0.737562 foot pounds, 0.239006 gram-calories (small calories), and 3.72506 x 10-7 horsepower-hours, and 0.000948451 B.t.u.

journeying.definition: the act or process of traveling from one place to another.

judging.definition: The cognitive process of reaching a decision or drawing conclusions.

judgmental.definition: depending on judgment; as, a judgmental error.

judo.definition: a sport adapted from jujitsu, originally a method of self-defense without weapons, and similar to wrestling; it was developed in Japan.

jumbo.definition: Any object which is a very large example of its class.

jumper.definition: to insert a jumper{2} between the two contacts in (a circuit). See 2nd jumper.

justified.definition: Arranged and spaced so as to line up at the left side or right side of the printed page, or on both sides; as, left justified; right justified.

vernal.definition: Of or pertaining to the spring; appearing in the spring; as, vernal bloom.

veterinarian.definition: One skilled in the treatment of diseases of cattle or domestic animals; a veterinary surgeon. Often abbreviated to vet.

videotape.definition: a video recording made on magnetic tape.

vives.definition: A disease of brute animals, especially of horses, seated in the glands under the ear, where a tumor is formed which sometimes ends in suppuration.

vivid.definition: True to the life; exhibiting the appearance of life or freshness; animated; spirited; bright; strong; intense; as, vivid colors.

zipper.definition: a device for locking together two toothed edges by means of a sliding tab.

zygote.definition: The cell resulting from the union of an ovum and a spermatozoon, or (broadly) the developing new organism arising from such a cell.

xerox.definition: To copy a printed document on a xerographic device.

xi.definition: The Roman number symbolizing the value eleven. Used after a noun it may symbolize the ordinal number; as, Superbowl XI.

xii.definition: The Roman number symbolizing the value twelve; denoting a quantity consisting of 12 items or units. Used after a noun it may symbolize the ordinal number; as, Superbowl XII.

xiii.definition: the Roman number symbolizing the value thirteen. Used after a noun it may symbolize the ordinal number; as, Superbowl XIII.

xl.definition: the Roman number symbolizing the value forty.

xv.definition: The Roman number symbolizing the value fifteen.

xvi.definition: The Roman number symbolizing the value sixteen.

xvii.definition: The Roman number symbolizing the value seventeen.

xviii.definition: The Roman number symbolizing the value eighteen.

xx.definition: The Roman number representing twenty; denoting a quantity consisting of 20 items or units.

fabricated.definition: formed or conceived by the fancy or imagination; as, a fabricated excuse for his absence.

facilitated.definition: freed from difficulty or impediment. Contrasted with delayed.

facilitative.definition: freeing from difficulty or impediment; as, facilitative changes in the economic structure.

factual.definition: of or pertaining to facts; as, factual inaccuracies.

faeces.definition: Excrement; ordure; also, settlings; sediment after infusion or distillation.

fag.definition: A male homosexual; -- always used disparagingly and considered offensive. Shortened form of faggot.

fallout.definition: the radioactive particles that settle to the ground after a nuclear explosion.

familial.definition: relating to or having the characteristics of a family; as, children of the same familial background; familial aggregation.

faraday.definition: the quantity of electric charge that, passed though an ionic solution, will cause electrolysis of one equivalent of ions; it is equal to about 96,490 coulombs. The number of univalent metal ions (such as silver in a silver nitrate solution) which would be deposited as free metal by such a current is Avogadro's number, 6.023 x 1023.

farmland.definition: a rural area where farming is practiced; land actually under cultivation or capable of supporting crops.

farthing.definition: The fourth of a penny; a small copper coin of Great Britain, being a cent in United States currency.

fascinated.definition: having the attention fixed by a sense of wonder.

fascinating.definition: capable of holding the attention; as, a fascinating story.

fascism.definition: a political theory advocating an authoritarian hierarchical government; -- opposed to democracy and liberalism.

fascist.definition: an adherent of fascism or similar right-wing authoritarian views.

favor.definition: Kind regard; propitious aspect; countenance; friendly disposition; kindness; good will.

fax.definition: To transmit a copy of a document (a fax) over a telephone line using facsimile devices or the telefax protocol at both ends. See fax, n., and facsimile{2}, n.

fealty.definition: Fidelity to one's lord; the feudal obligation by which the tenant or vassal was bound to be faithful to his lord; the special oath by which this obligation was assumed; fidelity to a superior power, or to a government; loyalty. It is no longer the practice to exact the performance of fealty, as a feudal obligation.

federated.definition: United by compact under a central organization, as governments or commercial organizations.

feedback.definition: the process in which part of the output of a system is returned to its input.

femoris.definition: The thigh bone; same as femur.

feral.definition: Wild; untamed; ferine; not domesticated; -- said of beasts, birds, and plants.

fertilized.definition: united with a male gamete to begin the development of an individual embryo; -- of female gametes.

fetch.definition: To bring one's self; to make headway; to veer; as, to fetch about; to fetch to windward.

fetching.definition: drawing favorable attention; as, a fetching new hat.

fete.definition: To feast; to honor with a festival.

feudal.definition: Of or pertaining to feuds, fiefs, or fees; as, feudal rights or services; feudal tenures.

fiberglass.definition: a material made of fine glass fibers woven into a fabric-like form, and used in applications requiring heat resistance; it is also embedded in resins to make a pliable but strong composite material used as the main component of fishing rods and boat hulls, and replacing the sheet metal in some automobile bodies.

field.definition: Cleared land; land suitable for tillage or pasture; cultivated ground; the open country.

fiend.definition: An implacable or malicious foe; one who is diabolically wicked or cruel; an infernal being; -- applied specifically to the devil or a demon.

fierceness.definition: the quality of being fierce; ferocity; fury; vehemence.

filled.definition: containing as much or as many as is possible or normal; as, filled to overflowing. Opposite of empty.

finalize.definition: to put the last touches on; put into final form.

finances.definition: assets in the form of money.

fine.definition: Finished; brought to perfection; refined; hence, free from impurity; excellent; superior; elegant; worthy of admiration; accomplished; beautiful.

fined.definition: subjected to punishment by a fine.

fingerprint.definition: to take an impression of the fingerprints of (a person); as, to fingerprint applicants for a gun permit.

fingerprinting.definition: The procedure of taking inked impressions of a person's fingerprints.

firelight.definition: the light of a fire (especially in a fireplace); as, lovers sitting together in the firelight.

firepower.definition: The relative capacity for delivering weapons fire on a target; as, the battleship has more firepower than a cruiser.

firstborn.definition: The first child born to a parent; as, his firstborn was showered with gifts from relatives.

flabby.definition: Yielding to the touch, and easily moved or shaken; hanging loose by its own weight; wanting firmness; flaccid; as, flabby flesh.

flaccid.definition: Yielding to pressure for want of firmness and stiffness; soft and weak; limber; lax; drooping; flabby; as, a flaccid muscle; flaccid flesh.

flared.definition: having a gradual increase in width; as, flared nostrils.

flashback.definition: a transition (in literary or theatrical works or films) to an earlier event or scene; also, the scene thus introduced.

flashlight.definition: a portable battery-powered electric lamp, small enough to be held in one hand; -- it is most commonly cylindrical, but other forms are also made. It is called in Britain a torch

flatness.definition: The quality or state of being flat.

flavoring.definition: something added to food primarily for the savor it imparts.

flavour.definition: same as flavor, v. and n..

flawed.definition: having flaws or imperfections; not perfect; -- applied broadly; as, a flawed vase; a flawed performance; a flawed character.

fledged.definition: having developed feathers or plumage; often used in combination; -- of birds.

fledgling.definition: having just acquired its flight feathers; -- of a young bird; as, a fledgling robin.

lien.definition: A charge, lien, etc., that successively attaches to such assets as a person may have from time to time, leaving him more or less free to dispose of or encumber them as if no such charge or lien existed.

flowered.definition: resembling or made of or suggestive of flowers.

fluctuating.definition: moving irregularly in an oscillatory manner, especially up and down; as, fluctuating prices.

fluorescein.definition: A yellowish red, crystalline substance, C20H12O5, produced by heating together phthalic anhydride and resorcin; -- so called, from the very brilliant yellowish green fluorescence of its alkaline solutions. It has acid properties, and its salts of the alkalies are known to the trade under the name of uranin.

fluoridation.definition: The addition of a fluoride to the water supply (to prevent dental decay).

flywheel.definition: A heavy wheel or disk which stores kinetic energy by rotating on a shaft, and by its momentum smoothes the operation of a reciprocating engine by reducing fluctuations of speed. It is used in certain types of machinery, such as automobiles.

foaming.definition: Giving off bubbles and developing a head of foam; as, a foaming glass of beer.

focused.definition: being in focus or brought into focus; clearly delineated; -- of an image. Opposite of unfocused.

focussing.definition: the concentration of attention or energy on something.

folded.definition: made compact by bending or doubling over.

footage.definition: the amount of film that has been shot.

football.definition: An inflated ball to be kicked in sport, usually made in India rubber, or a bladder incased in Leather.

footer.definition: a person who travels by foot.

forecasting.definition: The process of calculating and predicting future events, usually based on extrapolation from past experience, and with varying degress of uncertainty.

foregone.definition: past; -- used of time; as, foregone summers. Contrassted to present.

foreseeable.definition: being such as may reasonable be anticipated; as, foreseeable costs were well within the budget.

forested.definition: covered with forest; as, efforts to protect forested lands of the northwest.

forged.definition: Not genuine; counterfeit; -- used mostly of signatures and documents. See forge, v. t., 4.

formalities.definition: a set of procedures required to make a transaction official.

formalized.definition: concerned with or characterized by rigorous adherence to recognized forms, especially in religion or art; using formalism; as, highly formalized plays like "Waiting for Godot".

format.definition: to set into a specific format; -- of printed matter or data recorded on a data storage medium.

formulated.definition: reduced to a systematic form; reduced to a formula.

forthcoming.definition: Ready or about to appear; making appearance.

fossa.definition: A pit, groove, cavity, or depression, of greater or less depth; as, the temporal fossa on the side of the skull; the nasal foss containing the nostrils in most birds.

founded.definition: based; -- often used as combining terms; as, well-founded suspicions.

fractionation.definition: the act or process of separating a mixture into portions of different composition, as in distillation or fractional crystallization.

fragmentation.definition: the act or process of separating something into small pieces or fine particles.

frail.definition: Easily broken; fragile; not firm or durable; liable to fail and perish; easily destroyed; not tenacious of life; weak; infirm.

frailty.definition: The condition or quality of being frail, physically, mentally, or morally; frailness; infirmity; weakness of resolution; liableness to be deceived or seduced.

framed.definition: provided with a frame; as, there were framed snapshots of family and friends on her desk. Opposite of unframed.

frank.definition: To send by public conveyance free of expense.

frankfurter.definition: A small cooked sausage of beef or beef and pork, usually 5 to 6 inches, sometimes as long as 12 inches in length; called also frankforter, frankfort, frankfurt. It is commonly eaten on a roll, called a hot dog bun.

fray.definition: An angry quarrel; an affray; contest; combat; broil.

frills.definition: Ornamental objects of no great value.

frustrating.definition: preventing realization or attainment of a desire; causing frustration.

fucking.definition: unpleasant; annoying; -- also used as an informal intensifier.

fun.definition: Of or pertaining to fun; causing pleasure or amusement; as, a fun thing to do.

functionalism.definition: a psychology based on the assumption that all mental process are useful to an organism in adapting to the environment.

fundamentalism.definition: A system of beliefs based on the interpretation of every word in the Bible, both old and new testaments, as literal truth. It is primarily held by a branch of American Protestants.

funerary.definition: of or pertaining to a funeral or to burial of human remains; as, funerary urn.

furnished.definition: provided with necessary furnishings; -- used especially of rented apartments having furniture included in the rental price; as, a furnished apartment. Opposite of unfurnished.

furnishings.definition: the furniture and appliances and other movable accessories (including curtains and rugs) that make a home (or other building) livable.

furor.definition: an interest followed with exaggerated zeal; a fad.

fuselage.definition: The central, approximately cylindrical portion of an airplane which carries the passengers, crew, and cargo. It usually forms the main structural portion of an airplane, and to it are typically attached the wings, tail, and sometimes the engines. In single-propeller airplanes, the propeller is typically fixed at the front of the fuselage, although variants have been produced with the propeller at the rear. Some airplanes have no fuselage, properly so called.

quarterback.definition: To play the position of quarterback, in a football game.

gambling.definition: the act of playing for stakes in the hope of winning (including the payment of a price for a chance to win a prize); as, his gambling cost him a fortune.

gaming.definition: The act or practice of playing games for stakes or wagers; gambling.

gamma.definition: The third letter (G) of the Greek alphabet.

geisha.definition: A Japanese singing and dancing girl, trained to provide entertainment and company for a man or group of men.

gendarmerie.definition: The French police force; the body of gendarmes or gendarmes collectively.

genitalia.definition: The sex organs, especially the external sex organs, called the external genitalia; the genitals.

genocidal.definition: Of or pertaining to genocide; as, the genocidal policies of the Serbs in Bosnia.

genocide.definition: The systematic killing of a racial or cultural group; as, the Nazi genocide of Jews left few in Germany or Poland after World War II.

genotype.definition: A group of organisms sharing a specific genetic constitution.

genuine.definition: Belonging to, or proceeding from, the original stock; native;

geochemistry.definition: The study of the chemical composition of, and of actual or possible chemical changes in, the crust of the earth.

geography.definition: The science which treats of the world and its inhabitants; a description of the earth, or a portion of the earth, including its structure, features, products, political divisions, and the people by whom it is inhabited. It also includes the responses and adaptations of people to topography, climate, soil and vegetation

geophysical.definition: of or pertaining to geophysics; as, geophysical sciences.

geophysics.definition: A branch of geology that uses physical principles to study the properties of the earth.

geopolitics.definition: the study of the effects of economic geography on the powers of the state.

get.definition: A divorce granted by a Rabbi in accordance with Jewish law; also, the document attesting to the divorce.

gifted.definition: having unusual talent in some field.

giraffe.definition: An African ruminant (Giraffa camelopardalis formerly Camelopardalis giraffa) related to the deers and antelopes, but placed in a family (Giraffidae) by itself; the camelopard. It is the tallest of quadriped animals, being sometimes twenty feet from the hoofs to the top of the head. Its neck is very long, and its fore legs are much longer than its hind legs. There are three types, having different patterns of spots on the pelt and different territories: the Reticulated Giraffe, the Masai Giraffe, and the Uganda Giraffe. Intermediate crosses are also observed.

girlfriend.definition: any female friend; as, Mary and her girlfriend organized the party.

glamorous.definition: having an air of allure, romance and excitement; as, glamorous movie stars.

glinting.definition: having brief brilliant points or flashes of light; as, glinting eyes; glinting water.

glistening.definition: Reflecting light readily or in large amounts; having a surface luster; reflecting light directly rather than scattering it.

global.definition: involving the entire earth; not limited or provincial in scope; as, global war; global monetary policy.

globin.definition: a colorless protein obtained by removing heme from hemoglobin; the protein part of hemoglobin.

gloved.definition: having the hands covered with gloves. Opposite of gloveless.

goaded.definition: compelled forcibly by an outside agency; as, mobs goaded by blind hatred.

goddamned.definition: A more intense and vulgar form of darned; -- often taken as profane and offensive.

gonadotropin.definition: A hormone secreted by the pituitary gland and placenta, which stimulates the gonads and controls reproductive activity.

gonna.definition: Going to; as, who's gonna get the milk?.

google.definition: To search for Web pages containing a word or phrase, using the Google web site (www.google.com); as, I googled .

gotta.definition: Got to; have to; must; as, I gotta leave now.

graded.definition: ordered by some quantitative ranking; as, Reading tests of graded difficulty.

grantee.definition: The person to whom a grant or conveyance is made.

grantor.definition: The person by whom a grant or conveyance is made.

granular.definition: Consisting of, or resembling, grains; as, a granular substance.

grapefruit.definition: A citrus tree (Citrus paradisi) bearing large round edible fruit having a thick yellow rind and juicy somewhat acid pulp.

greased.definition: smeared with oil or grease to reduce friction; as, a greased pig is too slippery to hold.

groan.definition: To give forth a low, moaning sound in breathing; to utter a groan, as in pain, in sorrow, or in derision; to moan.

grooming.definition: Preparing a person for a position requiring skilled behavior, especially by providing opposrtunity for practise and guidance in making the right decisions; as, to provide grooming for one's successor as president.

grooved.definition: having grooves; as, a record is a grooved disk.

grosz.definition: a Polish monetary unit, equal to WordNet 1.5]

grotto.definition: A natural covered opening in the earth; a cave; also, an artificial recess, cave, or cavernlike apartment.

groundbreaking.definition: The ceremonial breaking of the ground to formally begin a construction project. It is sometimes carried out by an official who digs the first spadeful of dirt from the ground, to begin the preparatory excavation work.

grouped.definition: arranged into groups, each having some feature in common.

growing.definition: increasing in intensity of some quality.

guideline.definition: a formal rule describing how a situation must be handled; -- used as a direction to administrators from superiors.

guidelines.definition: a rule or set of rules giving guidance on how to behave in a situation.

guitarist.definition: a musician who plays the guitar.

gunshot.definition: Made by the shot of a gun; as, a gunshot wound.

guy.definition: A grotesque effigy, like that of Guy Fawkes, dressed up in England on the fifth of November, the day of the Gunpowder Plot.

gymnastics.definition: Athletic or disciplinary exercises; the art of performing gymnastic exercises.

gynecological.definition: Of or pertaining to gynecology; same as gynecological.

unconscious.definition: Usually the unconscious; that part of the mind in which mental processes occur that are not accesible to the awareness, but may significantly influence behavior.

underlying.definition: Lying under or beneath; as, the underlying strata of a locality.

unholy.definition: Not holy; unhallowed; not consecrated; hence, profane; wicked; impious.

update.definition: The event or process of updating (in either sense); the information provided in the process of updating; as, I gave the director the latest update on the project; the update took over an hour.

naive.definition: Having native or unaffected simplicity; ingenuous; artless; frank; as, na manners; a na person; na and unsophisticated remarks.

named.definition: given or having a specified name; as, an actor named Harold Lloyd; a building in Cardiff named the Temple of Peace. Contrasted to unnamed.

nanotechnology.definition: The manipulation or construction of objects with sizes in the nanometer range or smaller.

napa.definition: A plant (Brassica rapa pekinensis) with an elongated celerylike head of broadstalked leaves used as a vegetable in east Asia; called also Chinese cabbage.

narcissism.definition: An exceptional interest in and admiration for oneself.

narcissistic.definition: Having an excessive love of oneself; egocentric; egoistic.

narrate.definition: To tell, rehearse, or recite, as a story; to relate the particulars of; to go through with in detail, as an incident or transaction; to give an account of.

narration.definition: The act of telling or relating the particulars of an event; a recital of certain events, usually in chronological order; rehearsal.

narrowed.definition: reduced in size as if by being squeezed.

national.definition: A citizen (of a particular country); as, U. S. nationals are advised to contact their embassy when abroad.

nationalist.definition: One who advocates national unity and independence; -- as, for example, one of a party favoring Irish independence before 1918.

naturalist.definition: One versed in natural science; a student of natural history, esp. of the natural history of plants or animals; a botanist or zoologist.

naturalized.definition: Acclimated to a new environment; introduced from another region and persisting without cultivation; -- of plants or animals not native to a location.

nave.definition: The block in the center of a wheel, from which the spokes radiate, and through which the axle passes; -- called also hub or hob.

navigational.definition: of or pertaining to navigation; used in navigation; as, navigational aids.

nay.definition: No; -- a negative answer to a question asked, or a request made, now superseded by no. Opposed to aye or yea. See also Yes.

nearby.definition: situated near; as, the nearby towns. Opposite of far away.

nearer.definition: less distant in space; as, we walked to the nearer house.

neatness.definition: The state or quality of being neat.

necklace.definition: A string of beads, etc., or any continuous band or chain, worn around the neck as an ornament.

needed.definition: necessary; as, provided them with all needed equipment. Opposite of unnecessary.

neighbor.definition: To adjoin; to border on; to be near to.

nematode.definition: Any worm of the phylum Nematoda; a roundworm; -- they are unsegmented worms having a cylindrical elongated body. They may live freely in soil or water, or as parasites in plants or animals.

neocortex.definition: The cortical part of the neencephalon; the most recently evolved part of the cerebral cortex of the brain of higher animals, and the site of most of the higher brain functions; called also neopallium.

neoliberalism.definition: A political orientation originating in the 1960s, blending liberal political views with an emphasis on economic growth.

neonatal.definition: of or pertaining to a neonate; as, neonatal care; a neonatal unit at a hospital.

neonate.definition: A newborn child, especially one less than one month old.

nerve.definition: One of the whitish and elastic bundles of fibers, with the accompanying tissues, which transmit nervous impulses between nerve centers and various parts of the animal body.

netted.definition: resembling a net or a web.

network.definition: To connect together into a network; as, to network computers; to network the printer with computers.

networking.definition: Interchanging information or services, among a group; -- of persons or organizations.

neuropsychology.definition: the branch of psychology that is concerned with the physiological bases of psychological processes.

neuter.definition: To render incapable of sexual reproduction; to remove or alter the sexual organs so as to make infertile; to alter; to fix; to desex; -- in male animals, to castrate; in female animals, to spay.

newborn.definition: A baby recently born, usually less than one month old; a neonate.

newsprint.definition: Cheap paper made from wood pulp and used for printing newspapers.

newsroom.definition: A room where news is collected and disseminated, located in the offices of a newspaper, magazine, or news broadcast organization; as, the CBS newsroom.

newsworthy.definition: Sufficiently interesting to be reported in a newspaper; as, a dog biting a man is not a newsworthy item.

newton.definition: A unit of force of the Systeme Internationale system of units of measure, equal to the force that produces an acceleration of one meter per second per second when applied to a mass of one kilogram. Abbreviated N.

niacin.definition: A B vitamin (vitamin B5) essential for the normal function of the nervous system and the gastrointestinal tract. Called also nicotinic acid and antipellagra vitamin. Chemical formula C6H5NO2, chemically it is 3-pyridinecarboxylic acid.

nichts.definition: A quantity of no importance; nothing.

nickname.definition: A name given in affectionate familiarity, sportive familiarity, contempt, or derision; a familiar or an opprobrious appellation; as, Nicholas's nickname is Nick.

nigger.definition: A negro; -- in vulgar derision or depreciation. It is usually intended and interpreted as highly insulting and vulgar.

nightclub.definition: An establishment providing entertainment (as singers, dancers, or comedy acts), usually open late into the night or early morning, typically serving alcoholic beverages and food.

nightmarish.definition: Terrifying, as if in a nightmare{2}; resembling a nightmare{2}.

nine.definition: Eight and one more; one less than ten; as, nine miles.

nineties.definition: The decade from 1890 to 1899; as, the gay nineties.

niobium.definition: The chemical element of atomic number 41. Chemical symbol Nb. Atomic weight 92.91. Previously called columbium. See also Columbium.

no..definition: Number; -- the number designating place in an ordered sequence; as, no. 2.

noncommercial.definition: not connected with or engaged in commercial enterprises. Opposite of commercial.

nonlinear.definition: Not depictable graphically as a straight line; not changing by a constant amount for each unit of time, distance, or other independent variable. Opposite of linear.

nonpartisan.definition: free from party affiliation or bias. Opposite of partisan.

nonproductive.definition: not directly productive; as, nonproductive labor.

nonstop.definition: A flight made without intermediate landings between source and destination; as, how many nonstops are there to Dallas?.

nontechnical.definition: not characteristic of or skilled in applied arts and sciences; as, nontechnical aspects of the job; nontechnical training. Opposite of technical.

nonviolence.definition: The theory, doctrine, or practice of peaceful resistance to a government by fasting or refusing to cooperate.

nonviolent.definition: peacefully resistant in response to injustice; not using violence; -- used of protests and demonstrations; as, nonviolent resistance. Opposite of violent.

norepinephrine.definition: A hormone (C8H11NO3) secreted by the adrenal medulla; it also serves as a neurotransmitter, released at synapses; called also noradrenaline. Chemically it is 2-amino-1-(3,4-dihydroxyphenyl)ethanol. It is a precursor of epinephrine in the body.

normalcy.definition: The quality, state, or fact of being normal; the normal situation or condition; as, the point of normalcy.

normality.definition: Conformity with the norm; the state of being normal; the normal condition.

normalize.definition: To make normal; as, to normalize relations with China.

norman.definition: A wooden bar, or iron pin.

normative.definition: relating to or dealing with norms; as, normative discipline; normative samples.

nostalgia.definition: Homesickness; esp., a severe and sometimes fatal form of melancholia, due to homesickness.

nothings.definition: inconsequential conversation; as, they traded a few nothings as they parted.

notifying.definition: The act or process of informing by words.

nth.definition: Last or greatest in an indefinitely large series; as, to the nth degree.

nu.definition: The 13th letter of the Greek alphabet (WordNet 1.5]

nubia.definition: A light fabric of wool, worn on the head by women; a cloud.

nucleon.definition: A neutron or proton, when contained within an atomic nucleus.

nucleoside.definition: A type of molecule found in all living organisms, present mostly in chemically combined form as a component of nucleic acids, and also in smaller amounts in free form, consisting of a pentose sugar bound to a purine or pyrimidine base; two types of nucleoside, ribonucleoside and deoxyribonucleoside, are present. The most common bases present in nucleosides are adenine, cytosine, uracil, guanine, and thymine, and to a lesser extent hypoxanthine and other bases are found. The most common ribonucleosides composed from these bases are called adenosine, cytidine, uridine, and guanosine. The forms esterified with orthophosphoric at the 5-position of the pentose are called nucleotides. The nucleotides form the monomer units which are combined into DNA and RNA, which carry the genetic information required for reproduction in all known organisms.

nucleotide.definition: a phosphate ester of a nucleoside; one of the monomeric components of DNA or RNA.

numinous.definition: Evincing the presence of a deity; as, a numinous wood; the most numinous moment in the Mass.

nun.definition: The 25th letter of the Arabic alphabet, corresponding in pronunciation to n.

nursed.definition: fed mother's milk from the breast; -- of an infant.

nuts.definition: An expression of disapproval, defiance, or displeasure, as in:  [slang]PJC]

nylon.definition: Any of several thermoplastic polyamide plastics, comprising a family of high-strength resilient synthetic materials, used mostly in fibers.

sentential.definition: Comprising sentences; as, a sentential translation.

shrug.definition: A gesture consisting of drawing up the shoulders, -- a motion usually expressing doubt, indifference, or dislike; -- it is sometimes accompanied by a slight turning of the hands outward or upward. Such a gesture may be made, as in answering "who knows" to a question, suggesting utter ignorance of an answer and a disinclination to pursue the topic further.

sibling.definition: of or pertaining to a sibling, n.; as, sibling rivalry: the common rivalry between siblings.

signing.definition: The procedure or process of communicating by use of a sign language.

singles.definition: For unmarried persons, or catering especially to unmarried persons; as, a singles bar; a singles party.

sliver.definition: To cut or divide into long, thin pieces, or into very small pieces; to cut or rend lengthwise; to slit; as, to sliver wood.

soul.definition: By or for African-Americans, or characteristic of their culture; as, soul music; soul newspapers; soul food.

spacecraft.definition: a vehicle capable of travelling in or into outer space; at present, all such vehicles are powered by rocket engine.

spanking.definition: Moving with a quick, lively pace, or capable of so doing; dashing.

spar.definition: An old name for a nonmetallic mineral, usually cleavable and somewhat lustrous; as, calc spar, or calcite, fluor spar, etc. It was especially used in the case of the gangue minerals of a metalliferous vein.

specific.definition: Of or pertaining to a species; characterizing or constituting a species; possessing the peculiar property or properties of a thing which constitute its species, and distinguish it from other things; as, the specific form of an animal or a plant; the specific qualities of a drug; the specific distinction between virtue and vice.

specification.definition: The act of specifying or determining by a mark or limit; notation of limits.

sprawl.definition: The position or state resulting from sprawling; as, he sat on the couch in a sprawl; uncontrolled urban sprawl.

standoff.definition: Serving to keep two objects or parts of a machine separated; as, a standoff insulator.

stands.definition: a structure (often made of wood and sometimes temporary) with seats or benches where people can sit to watch an event (such as a game or parade).

staple.definition: To sort according to its staple; as, to staple cotton.

stare.definition: To look with fixed eyes wide open, as through fear, wonder, surprise, impudence, etc.; to fasten an earnest and prolonged gaze on some object.

stator.definition: A stationary part in or about which another part (the rotor) revolves, esp. when both are large;

stout.definition: A strong, dark malt brew having a higher percentage of hops than porter; strong porter; a popular variety sold in the U. S. is Guinness' stout.

streamline.definition: to design or modify so as to present the least possible resistance to fluid flow; -- used mostly of vehicles, such as automobiles, airplanes, or ships.

supersonic.definition: Moving at a speed greater than the speed of sound in air; -- this speed varies with altitude, since the speed of sound varies with altitude, as well as with temperature and humidity, being approximately 1129 feet per second at sea level and 984 feet per second at 16 miles altitude.

switchboard.definition: an elctrical apparatus consisting predominantly of a panel on which are switches or other means of completing electrical circuits; -- used especially for the devices used in telephone exchanges. See sense 2.

wager.definition: To hazard on the issue of a contest, or on some question that is to be decided, or on some eventuality; to lay; to stake; to bet.

wanna.definition: Want to; as, I wanna go home.

web.definition: The world-wide web; -- usually referred to as the web.

wick.definition: To strike a stone in an oblique direction.

wise.definition: Way of being or acting; manner; mode; fashion.

witch.definition: To bewitch; to fascinate; to enchant.

worthwhile.definition: Worth the time or effort spent.

radar.definition: An electronic device designed to detect objects at a distance, and determine their distance from the device, by transmitting a pulse of radio waves and measuring the time required for the echo of the pulse to return to the emitting device; as, the radar showed a plane approaching rapidly.

radioactive.definition: Capable of luminescence under the action of cathode rays, X rays, or any of the allied forms of radiation.

radioactivity.definition: a form of instability which is a property of the atomic nuclei of certain isotopes, which causes a spontaneous change in the structure of the nucleus, accompanied by emission of energetic radiation. The radiation emitted is usually sufficient to cause ionization in matter through which it passes, and is therefore called ionizing radiation. The radiation emitted by most radioactive substances is one of three types: alpha rays, beta rays, or gamma rays. Some chemical elements have no stable isotopes, and these are referred to as radioactive elements, and the element itself is said to possess radioactivity.

radiography.definition: Art or process of making radiographs, radiograms, or autoradiograms.

ras.definition: The name and genetic symbol for a mutant gene that has been identified as one of those associated with certains types of cancer; -- it is a form of oncogene. It was first observed in rats, but analogues have been found in humans and other animals.

redemption.definition: The act of redeeming, or the state of being redeemed; repurchase; ransom; release; rescue; deliverance; as, the redemption of prisoners taken in war; the redemption of a ship and cargo.

reevaluate.definition: To revise or renew one's assessment; to evaluate again.

refute.definition: To disprove and overthrow by argument, evidence, or countervailing proof; to prove to be false or erroneous; to confute; as, to refute arguments; to refute testimony; to refute opinions or theories; to refute a disputant.

regroup.definition: To reorganize into new groups; to reform a group that has been dispersed. The spelling without the hyphen is more common.

relativity.definition: The state of being relative; as, the relativity of a subject.

reorganize.definition: To organize again or anew; as, to reorganize a society or an army.

reread.definition: To rad again; as, He re-read her letters to him.

research.definition: To search or examine with continued care; to seek diligently.

resiliency.definition: The act of springing back, rebounding, or resiling; as, the resilience of a ball or of sound.

rubella.definition: An acute but mild viral infection characterized by a dusky red cutaneous eruption resembling that of measles, but attended by only mild respiratory problems or fever; -- called also German measles. The infective virus is called Rubella virus, or Rubivirus. If contracted by a woman during the first several months of pregnancy, rubella may cause serious abnormalities in the fetus.

ibuprofen.definition: a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory medicine used to relieve the pain of arthritis and as an analgesic and antipyretic; Advil and Motrin and Nuprin are trademarks of brands of ibuprofen tablets.

ice.definition: To cover with ice; to convert into ice, or into something resembling ice.

icon.definition: An image or representation; a portrait or pretended portrait.

id.definition: That part of a person's psyche which is the unconscious source of impulses seeking gratification or pleasure; the impulses are usually modified by the ego and superego before being acted upon.

identifying.definition: serving to distinguish or identify an object, person, species or group; as, we were asked to describe any identifying marks or distinguishing features.

ideological.definition: concerned with or suggestive of ideas; as, an ideologic argument.

illuminated.definition: rendered luminous by rays of light striking and reflecting; -- used especially of illumination by artificial light.

illustrated.definition: provided with pictures; -- of a publication; as, an illustrated weekly. Opposite of unillustrated.

imagined.definition: existing in the mind only; not real or actual; as, her imagined fame.

immobilization.definition: The act or process of limiting movement or making incapable of movement; as, immobilization of the injured knee was necessary; the storm caused complete immobilization of the rescue team.

immunization.definition: the act of making immune (especially by inoculation).

immunized.definition: rendered less susceptible (to disease) by treatment with a vaccine.

immunoglobulin.definition: any one of a class of globular proteins which are antibodies and are produced by the immune system in animals.

immunology.definition: The science which studies the immune system, the processes of immunity, and the nature of the immune response, and techniques of analysis which use the immune response.

imperialistic.definition: Of, pertaining to, or advocating imperialism.

implicated.definition: culpably involved; connected; -- of persons with respect to responsibility for events.

implicating.definition: a charge that implicates someone (usually of wrongdoing).

imported.definition: brought into the country from a foreign source; -- used of especially merchandise; -- correlative of exported.

imposed.definition: p. p. of impose; as, rules imposed by society.

impressed.definition: having the conscious mind deeply or markedly affected or influenced; -- usually used with by or with.

imprinting.definition: The learning of a behavioral pattern that occurs soon after birth or hatching in certain animals, in which a long-lasting response to an individual (such as a parent) or an object is rapidly acquired; it is particularly noted in the response of certain birds to the animal they first see after hatching, usually the parent, as in ducks who will follow the adult duck they first see.

improved.definition: advanced to a more desirable or valuable or excellent state. Opposite of unimproved.

inactivate.definition: to make inactive; as, boiling will inactivate most enzymes; acetylation of the antibiotic inactivated it.

inactivation.definition: The act or process of inactivating.

increased.definition: made greater in size or amount or degree. Opposite of decreased.

increasing.definition: becoming greater or larger; as, increasing prices.

incriminating.definition: charging or suggestive of guilt or blame; as, incriminating testimony; incriminating evidence.

indentured.definition: Bound by contract to work for another for a specified period of time.

indexation.definition: a system of economic regulation in which wages and interest are tied to the cost-of-living index in order to compensate for the effects of inflation.

individualist.definition: a person who pursues independent thought or action.

indomethacin.definition: A nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory, antipyretic and analgesic substance (C19H16ClNO4) prepared synthetically and used for the treatment of pain and arthritis. It blocks prostaglandin biosynthesis. Chemically, it is 1-(4-chlorobenzoyl)-5-methoxy-2-methyl-1H-indole-3-acetic acid.

induced.definition: brought about or caused; not spontaneous; as, a case of steroid-induced weakness. Contrasted to spontaneous.

inhaled.definition: drawn into the lungs; breathed in; as, inhaled smoke can damage the lungs. Inverse of exhaled.

inherited.definition: tending to occur among members of a family usually by heredity; as, an inherited disease.

inhibited.definition: held back or restrained or prevented; as, in certain conditions previously inhibited conditioned reactions can reappear; -- of behaviors. Opposite of uninhibited.

inhibiting.definition: discouraging (a person) from action by threat of punishment; as, an overly strict or inhibiting discipline.

inhumane.definition: not humane; lacking and reflecting lack of pity, kindness, or compassion; as, humans are innately inhumane; this explains much of the misery and suffering in the world; biological weapons are considered too inhumane to be used.

initialize.definition: to assign an initial value to (a variable or set of variables in a computer program); as, many bugs are caused by a failure to initialize variables.

injured.definition: having received an injury;-- usually used of physical or mental injury to persons. Opposite of uninjured.

inositol.definition: A white crystalline substance (C6H12O6) with a sweet taste, widely distributed in certain animal tissues and fluids, particularly in the muscles of the heart and lungs, and also in some plants, as in unripe pease, beans, potato sprouts, etc. Although isomeric with dextrose, it has no carbonyl (aldehyde or ketone) group, and is therefore not a carbohydrate, but a derivative of cyclohexane. Called also inosite, cyclohexitol, cyclohexanehexol, hexahydroxycyclohexane and phaseomannite. There are nine possible steroisomers, not all of which are found naturally. The predominate natural form is cis-1,2,3,5-trans-4,6-cyclohexanehexol, also called myo-inositol. The naturally occurring phytic acid in plants is the hexaphosphate of inositol, from which inositol may be manufactured; phytin is the calcium-magnesium salt of phytic acid. It is also a component of phosphatidylinositol.

insider.definition: an officer of a corporation or others who have access to private information about the corporation's operations, especially information relating to profitability.

insightful.definition: having intellectual depth; having or showing an exceptional degree of insight{2}; -- of people or their comments.

installing.definition: the act of installing something (as equipment).

integrated.definition: Formed or united into a whole.

integrating.definition: the action of incorporating a racial or religious group into a community.

integrative.definition: tending to combine and coordinate diverse elements into a whole.

intelligentsia.definition: an educated and intellectual{2} elite; intellectuals, collectively or considered as a class.

intensified.definition: made more severe or intense, especially in law.

interconnectedness.definition: a state of being connected reciprocally.

interface.definition: a surface forming a common boundary between two things, especially between two fluids.

interfaith.definition: involving persons of different religious faiths; as, an interfaith marriage; interfaith good will.

interlocking.definition: Connected together in such a manner that the parts work together as a single unit, or in a coordianted manner.

intern.definition: A resident physician in a hospital, especially one who has recently received the Doctorate and is practising under supervision of experienced physicians, as a continuation of the training process; a house physician; also called houseman in Britain.

internalization.definition: learning (of values or attitudes etc.) that is incorporated within yourself.

internationalization.definition: the act of bringing something under international control.

internet.definition: A large network{3} of numerous computers connected through a number of major nodes of high-speed computers having high-speed communications channels between the major nodes, and numerous minor nodes allowing electronic communication among millions of computers around the world; -- usually referred to as the internet. It is the basis for the World-Wide Web.

internship.definition: The state of being an intern; the position of an intern.

interoperability.definition: The quality of being interoperable. Used of data structures or executable programs.

intersecting.definition: having at least one spatial point in common.

interstate.definition: An interstate highway, part of the United States Interstate Highway system.

intima.definition: the innermost coat of an organ, such as a blood vessel. It usually consists of an endothelial layer of cells, backed by connective tissue and elastic tissue.

intimal.definition: of or pertaining to the intima.

intimidated.definition: made timid or fearful as by threats.

intimidating.definition: discouraging; inhibiting; deterring. Opposite of encouraging.

introverted.definition: examining one's own sensory and perceptual experiences. Contrasted with extrospective.

investigating.definition: the work of inquiring into something thoroughly and systematically.

investigatory.definition: Of or pertaining to an investigation; accomplished by investigation; designed to find information or ascertain facts; as, investigatory committee; the investigatory excesses of the prosecutor.

investing.definition: the act or process of expending resources, especially money, to achieve rewards.

ionic.definition: Of or pertaining to ions; composed of ions, containing ions, or breaking down into ions when dissolved in a polar solvent; as, an ionic solution will conduct a current of electricity. Opposite of nonionic.

ionized.definition: converted totally or partly into ions. Opposite of nonionized and unionized.

ionosphere.definition: the outer region of the earth's atmosphere, beyond which is the exosphere; it contains a high concentration of free electrons and ions, and extends from about 50 miles to about 250 miles above the earth's surface, but the height shows daily and seasonal variation, and the composition of the particles in the ionosphere is also affected by events such as solar flares.

iridium.definition: A rare metallic element of atomic number 77, of the same group as platinum, which it much resembles, being silver-white and indifferent to most corrosive agents, but harder, more brittle, and with a higher melting temperature (24101913 Webster +PJC]

irrationality.definition: The quality or state of being irrational; absence of rationality.

irritated.definition: aroused to impatience or anger; as, made an irritated gesture.

isolationism.definition: The doctrine or policy of minimal participation by one's country in international economic and political relations, specifically by not entering into alliances or other international agreements, in order to avoid becoming entangled in foreign wars, and to be able to devote the nation's energies primarily to advancing its own domestic interests.

isolationist.definition: A proponent or supporter of isolationism; one who is isolationistic.

issuing.definition: the act of issuing; putting out.

itinerary.definition: Itinerant; traveling; passing from place to place; done on a journey.

itself.definition: The neuter reflexive pronoun of It; as, the thing is good in itself; it stands by itself.

ix.definition: The Roman numerals signifying nine; denoting a quantity consisting of one more than eight and one less than ten.
